WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:03:03.758 --> 00:03:05.159
Very good.

3
00:03:05.259 --> 00:03:09.880
Exquisitely worked.
You've created a jewel. my boy.

4
00:03:09.964 --> 00:03:15.185
Perfect for a courtesan or priest
to pluck after supper.

5
00:03:15.269 --> 00:03:18.922
or polish Sundays after mass.

6
00:03:19.006 --> 00:03:20.174
In other words...

7
00:03:20.274 --> 00:03:24.438
this violin will never bear my name.

8
00:03:27.882 --> 00:03:31.648
Put your anger into your work. my boy.

9
00:03:32.086 --> 00:03:35.055
Stay with me and learn.

10
00:03:49.303 --> 00:03:51.855
1 million. 1.600.000.

11
00:03:51.939 --> 00:03:53.541
$1.600.000.

12
00:03:53.641 --> 00:03:57.127
Bids to all now. at 1.600.000...

13
00:03:57.211 --> 00:03:59.013
1.650.000.

14
00:03:59.113 --> 00:04:03.300
1.650.000.
1.675.000.

15
00:04:03.384 --> 00:04:05.602
Is that a bid. sir?
Don't be shy.

16
00:04:05.686 --> 00:04:09.373
All right then. I'll take it.
1.700.000.

17
00:04:09.457 --> 00:04:12.709
1.725.000.
1.725.000.

18
00:04:12.793 --> 00:04:14.562
1.750.000.
Thank you.

19
00:04:14.662 --> 00:04:16.430
The bid is $1.750.000.

20
00:04:16.530 --> 00:04:19.316
-1.775.000 on my left.
-Mr. Morritz.

21
00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:23.520
Please don't let me forget this.

22
00:04:23.604 --> 00:04:26.156
1.775.000 on my left.

23
00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:27.675
Against the telephone now.

24
00:04:27.775 --> 00:04:31.061
Against you. sir.
1.775.000.

25
00:04:31.145 --> 00:04:34.164
1.810.000?
1.810.000.

26
00:04:34.248 --> 00:04:38.669
1.850.000.
1.875.000 on my left.

27
00:04:38.753 --> 00:04:40.221
In the room...

28
00:04:40.321 --> 00:04:42.439
1.900.000?

29
00:04:42.523 --> 00:04:44.225
1.920.000 in the room.

30
00:04:44.325 --> 00:04:47.411
Yes. I got you. sir.
1.940.000.

31
00:04:47.495 --> 00:04:50.614
Not yours. ma'am.
Neither of yours.

32
00:04:50.698 --> 00:04:54.327
$1.940.000.

33
00:04:54.935 --> 00:04:55.670
I'll take 10.

34
00:04:55.770 --> 00:04:58.822
Do you want back in. sir?
Is that a yes? No?

35
00:04:58.906 --> 00:05:03.627
The Stradivarius now at $1.940.000.

36
00:05:03.711 --> 00:05:05.629
1.950.000 on my left.

37
00:05:05.713 --> 00:05:06.781
Down to you two.

38
00:05:06.881 --> 00:05:09.766
1.950.000.
Not yours. sir?

39
00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:14.238
Not yours?
1.950.000.

40
00:05:14.322 --> 00:05:16.090
All done then?

41
00:05:16.190 --> 00:05:17.558
Fair warning.

42
00:05:17.658 --> 00:05:21.044
I'm selling now at $1.950.000.

43
00:05:21.128 --> 00:05:25.292
And sold to the lady on my left.

44
00:05:32.907 --> 00:05:36.493
The last sale of the evening.
lot number 72.

45
00:05:36.577 --> 00:05:38.528
on the turntable there.

46
00:05:38.612 --> 00:05:40.481
The star of the night...

47
00:05:40.581 --> 00:05:42.083
and... where is she?

48
00:05:42.183 --> 00:05:47.437
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti. 1681.

49
00:05:47.521 --> 00:05:49.940
A masterpiece of the Golden Age.

50
00:05:50.024 --> 00:05:54.358
And. if she will give us the pleasure.

51
00:05:55.363 --> 00:05:57.914
And here she is now. lot 72.

52
00:05:57.998 --> 00:06:02.152
the so-called Red Violin.

53
00:06:02.236 --> 00:06:04.655
At this time the last order bid

54
00:06:04.739 --> 00:06:06.207
is at $250.000.

55
00:06:06.307 --> 00:06:08.992
A lot of interest here. of course.

56
00:06:09.076 --> 00:06:11.662
So. now let's open the floor
and who will start us off?

57
00:06:11.746 --> 00:06:14.665
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

58
00:06:14.749 --> 00:06:18.082
270.000...

59
00:06:41.575 --> 00:06:43.575
Madame?

60
00:06:47.014 --> 00:06:49.766
Cesca. can you still see the future?

61
00:06:49.850 --> 00:06:52.035
Are you all right?

62
00:06:52.119 --> 00:06:53.354
Sit down.

63
00:06:53.454 --> 00:06:56.340
Did you call me?
I was in the garden.

64
00:06:56.424 --> 00:06:59.276
-I can come here. can't I?
-Of course.

65
00:06:59.360 --> 00:07:03.797
-This is part of my house.
-Of course. madame.

66
00:07:05.933 --> 00:07:06.901
I have...

67
00:07:07.001 --> 00:07:11.870
some new amulets and bones for you.

68
00:07:12.173 --> 00:07:17.509
If your husband spits on them.
it will help.

69
00:07:18.245 --> 00:07:19.814
Are you hungry?

70
00:07:19.914 --> 00:07:22.866
Don't eat that. it's fish.

71
00:07:22.950 --> 00:07:23.517
So?

72
00:07:23.617 --> 00:07:28.350
Your child will be slow to learn.

73
00:07:30.858 --> 00:07:33.944
I also have some stones for you...

74
00:07:34.028 --> 00:07:37.447
and a key to wear around your neck.

75
00:07:37.531 --> 00:07:39.649
My husband's tired of spitting.

76
00:07:39.733 --> 00:07:42.185
Spitting's what men are good for.

77
00:07:42.269 --> 00:07:46.535
A father's saliva... the
best thing he can give.

78
00:07:47.575 --> 00:07:48.676
Cesca...

79
00:07:48.776 --> 00:07:52.007
tell me my child's future.

80
00:07:52.246 --> 00:07:53.881
I can't do that.

81
00:07:53.981 --> 00:07:56.199
Don't worry about my husband.

82
00:07:56.283 --> 00:07:59.736
It's not your husband.

83
00:07:59.820 --> 00:08:03.256
I'm simply not able to do it.

84
00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:05.960
I see.

85
00:08:06.060 --> 00:08:08.945
Until the baby is born...

86
00:08:09.029 --> 00:08:12.362
your humors are one.

87
00:08:13.400 --> 00:08:15.493
However...

88
00:08:16.203 --> 00:08:18.221
I can read your future.

89
00:08:18.305 --> 00:08:21.024
No. I told you. I'm scared.

90
00:08:21.108 --> 00:08:23.508
Come on. madame.

91
00:08:24.211 --> 00:08:26.236
Five cards.

92
00:08:28.716 --> 00:08:31.480
It's only the future.

93
00:08:31.619 --> 00:08:33.985
What if it's bad?

94
00:08:34.355 --> 00:08:37.415
I'll pretend not to see it.

95
00:08:59.947 --> 00:09:01.947
Tell me everything.

96
00:09:11.091 --> 00:09:13.091
The moon.

97
00:09:14.061 --> 00:09:15.196
You'll live...

98
00:09:15.296 --> 00:09:20.598
a long life. full and rich.

99
00:09:21.702 --> 00:09:23.720
There's...

100
00:09:23.804 --> 00:09:26.830
there's travel ahead.

101
00:09:27.808 --> 00:09:29.543
I see...

102
00:09:29.643 --> 00:09:32.237
a long journey.

103
00:09:38.452 --> 00:09:40.452
Niccolò?

104
00:09:42.890 --> 00:09:44.890
Leave us.

105
00:09:49.029 --> 00:09:51.122
Close the door.

106
00:09:53.968 --> 00:09:54.435
What is it?

107
00:09:54.535 --> 00:09:58.388
Why do you come here in your condition?

108
00:09:58.472 --> 00:10:01.324
-I know I'll find you here.
-What is it?

109
00:10:01.408 --> 00:10:04.027
-I talked to Cesca.
-And?

110
00:10:04.111 --> 00:10:05.713
She read my future.

111
00:10:05.813 --> 00:10:06.981
Cesca! Dear God!

112
00:10:07.081 --> 00:10:12.235
And the birth. she said. will be
very difficult. and painful.

113
00:10:12.319 --> 00:10:13.854
They always are.

114
00:10:13.954 --> 00:10:16.891
-This is no prediction!
-We're talking about me!

115
00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:21.011
Why do you listen to Cesca?
She is our servant.

116
00:10:21.095 --> 00:10:24.981
I have an excellent midwife.
an astrologer. a doctor.

117
00:10:25.065 --> 00:10:27.918
They'll all be there.
It will be perfect.

118
00:10:28.002 --> 00:10:31.388
-I know.
-How do you know?

119
00:10:31.472 --> 00:10:33.472
I know.

120
00:10:42.583 --> 00:10:46.212
I'm too old to be having a baby.

121
00:11:09.643 --> 00:11:11.941
This is a violin.

122
00:11:15.716 --> 00:11:20.119
-It's different.
-I still have to varnish it.

123
00:11:20.821 --> 00:11:23.206
But there's something...

124
00:11:23.290 --> 00:11:24.758
It's perfect.

125
00:11:24.858 --> 00:11:26.343
Everything else here is junk...

126
00:11:26.427 --> 00:11:30.814
worthy of a peddler. or the trash heap.

127
00:11:30.898 --> 00:11:33.662
But this is my masterpiece.

128
00:11:35.836 --> 00:11:38.488
I made it for our son. Anna.

129
00:11:38.572 --> 00:11:41.491
Our son will be a musician.

130
00:11:41.575 --> 00:11:43.793
He'll live for music.

131
00:11:43.877 --> 00:11:48.644
He'll bring us pride.
and beauty to the world.

132
00:11:49.483 --> 00:11:53.837
I wanted to surprise you. but you see...

133
00:11:53.921 --> 00:11:56.740
I can also make predictions.

134
00:11:56.824 --> 00:11:59.918
It's too big for a baby.

135
00:12:01.562 --> 00:12:03.689
He'll grow.

136
00:12:13.574 --> 00:12:17.408
My child will come when the moon is full.

137
00:12:17.644 --> 00:12:18.946
Come to bed.

138
00:12:19.046 --> 00:12:21.965
You're jealous of our relationship.

139
00:12:22.049 --> 00:12:23.751
Me and the moon.

140
00:12:23.851 --> 00:12:26.403
No. I'm not jealous.

141
00:12:26.487 --> 00:12:29.047
I know you'll come back.

142
00:14:12.226 --> 00:14:15.145
Master. a boy is asking for you.

143
00:14:15.229 --> 00:14:16.630
Tell him to go away.

144
00:14:16.730 --> 00:14:20.116
He won't. sir.
The doctor sent him.

145
00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.118
I think you'd better come.

146
00:14:22.202 --> 00:14:24.187
Your wife. sir... the doctor...

147
00:14:24.271 --> 00:14:27.257
-What is it?
-She's not well.

148
00:14:27.341 --> 00:14:29.775
Having the baby.

149
00:15:30.270 --> 00:15:32.270
Get out.

150
00:15:32.439 --> 00:15:36.933
Get out! Leave me alone.
for God's sake!

151
00:18:20.974 --> 00:18:23.192
1.650.000.

152
00:18:23.276 --> 00:18:25.728
1.675.000.

153
00:18:25.812 --> 00:18:28.248
Is that a bid. sir?
Don't be shy. I'll take it.

154
00:18:28.348 --> 00:18:30.199
-1.700.000...
-Excuse me. Mr. Ruselsky.

155
00:18:30.283 --> 00:18:31.585
1.725.000.

156
00:18:31.685 --> 00:18:34.404
The Stradivarius now at 1.725.000.

157
00:18:34.488 --> 00:18:36.472
Paul at 1.750.000.

158
00:18:36.556 --> 00:18:38.775
1.775.000 on the left.

159
00:18:38.859 --> 00:18:41.194
Against the telephone now.
Against you. sir.

160
00:18:41.294 --> 00:18:43.713
1.775.000.
1.810.000.

161
00:18:43.797 --> 00:18:46.315
1.810.000.
1.850.000.

162
00:18:46.399 --> 00:18:49.552
1.850.000.
1.875.000.

163
00:18:49.636 --> 00:18:53.523
-1.900.000...
-Son of a bitch.

164
00:18:53.607 --> 00:18:56.959
-He knows nothing.
-Who? Who?

165
00:18:57.043 --> 00:18:57.978
Morritz.

166
00:18:58.078 --> 00:19:00.496
$1.940.000.

167
00:19:00.580 --> 00:19:03.599
1.950.000 on the left.

168
00:19:03.683 --> 00:19:04.651
All done then?

169
00:19:04.751 --> 00:19:08.805
I'm selling now at $1.950.000.

170
00:19:08.889 --> 00:19:12.689
And sold to the lady on my left.

171
00:19:18.965 --> 00:19:21.184
Now. ladies and gentlemen.
the last sale of the evening.

172
00:19:21.268 --> 00:19:24.654
lot number 72. the star of the night...

173
00:19:24.738 --> 00:19:25.872
where is she?

174
00:19:25.972 --> 00:19:30.226
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti. 1681.

175
00:19:30.310 --> 00:19:32.628
A masterpiece of the Golden Age.

176
00:19:32.712 --> 00:19:34.714
If she will give us the pleasure.

177
00:19:34.814 --> 00:19:39.368
And there she is now. lot number 72.

178
00:19:39.452 --> 00:19:41.771
the so-called Red Violin.

179
00:19:41.855 --> 00:19:44.707
The last order bid is at $250.000.

180
00:19:44.791 --> 00:19:47.043
Who will start us off?
260.000.

181
00:19:47.127 --> 00:19:49.254
Good evening.
Mr. Ruselsky.

182
00:20:38.945 --> 00:20:42.403
You must clean the violin every day.

183
00:20:43.016 --> 00:20:44.551
Care for it well.

184
00:20:44.651 --> 00:20:49.884
This is your violin for as long
as you're at the orphanage.

185
00:22:04.397 --> 00:22:07.149
A curse hangs over you. madame.

186
00:22:07.233 --> 00:22:11.821
Danger to those who
come under your thrall.

187
00:22:11.905 --> 00:22:14.523
And there will be many...

188
00:22:14.607 --> 00:22:16.409
many.

189
00:22:16.509 --> 00:22:21.003
It is a powerful card. the Hanged Man.

190
00:22:21.548 --> 00:22:24.767
I see... I see danger...

191
00:22:24.851 --> 00:22:28.116
infirmity and disease.

192
00:22:29.489 --> 00:22:33.323
I'm sorry. but what kind I can't say.

193
00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:37.360
There are many kinds of sickness.

194
00:22:59.686 --> 00:23:02.438
These roads. Brother Christophe!

195
00:23:02.522 --> 00:23:07.176
You've no idea what I've endured.
And why such haste?

196
00:23:07.260 --> 00:23:12.481
What is so urgent it couldn't
wait until my next visit?

197
00:23:12.565 --> 00:23:14.134
We have a boy. sir.

198
00:23:14.234 --> 00:23:15.935
You have many boys!

199
00:23:16.035 --> 00:23:18.921
This boy is a miracle.
You'll see.

200
00:23:19.005 --> 00:23:21.924
Vienna swarms with miracles.

201
00:23:22.008 --> 00:23:23.009
Not like him.

202
00:23:23.109 --> 00:23:26.567
We felt you should see him at once.

203
00:23:27.080 --> 00:23:28.515
Does he speak French?

204
00:23:28.615 --> 00:23:30.383
No. sir. Unfortunately.

205
00:23:30.483 --> 00:23:34.203
All your students should learn French.

206
00:23:34.287 --> 00:23:36.505
It's the language of music.

207
00:23:36.589 --> 00:23:40.753
It hones the ear and elevates the mind!

208
00:23:55.642 --> 00:23:57.377
Monsieur Poussin...

209
00:23:57.477 --> 00:24:00.275
this is Kaspar Weiss.

210
00:24:03.283 --> 00:24:06.202
What violin is this?

211
00:24:06.286 --> 00:24:08.938
I haven't seen it before.

212
00:24:09.022 --> 00:24:11.640
We've had it for 100 years.

213
00:24:11.724 --> 00:24:13.593
Far too big for him.

214
00:24:13.693 --> 00:24:15.495
Look at his hands.

215
00:24:15.595 --> 00:24:18.614
He should play on a child's violin.

216
00:24:18.698 --> 00:24:20.333
Even Mozart...

217
00:24:20.433 --> 00:24:23.036
God rest his soul. played in Versailles...

218
00:24:23.136 --> 00:24:25.154
on a child's violin.

219
00:24:25.238 --> 00:24:27.523
No shame in that.

220
00:24:27.607 --> 00:24:30.893
Wouldn't you like a smaller instrument?

221
00:24:30.977 --> 00:24:33.309
He seems to manage.

222
00:24:34.681 --> 00:24:37.673
Let him try.

223
00:24:38.551 --> 00:24:40.551
Play. my boy.

224
00:24:40.854 --> 00:24:42.854
Play.

225
00:26:15.548 --> 00:26:17.548
I see.

226
00:26:22.388 --> 00:26:24.373
Monsieur Poussin?

227
00:26:24.457 --> 00:26:29.345
We're prepared to offer a small sum

228
00:26:29.429 --> 00:26:32.489
to help him in his study.

229
00:26:51.317 --> 00:26:56.705
They say you're a good boy.
well-mannered and clean.

230
00:26:56.789 --> 00:26:58.358
Glad to hear it.

231
00:26:58.458 --> 00:27:00.743
But you don't like vegetables.

232
00:27:00.827 --> 00:27:02.262
Is that so?

233
00:27:02.362 --> 00:27:03.796
Yes. sir.

234
00:27:03.896 --> 00:27:05.365
What don't you like?

235
00:27:05.465 --> 00:27:07.816
Carrots. sir...

236
00:27:07.900 --> 00:27:10.452
and beans and cabbage...

237
00:27:10.536 --> 00:27:12.536
These monks can't cook.

238
00:27:15.575 --> 00:27:18.394
They also write you've a weak heart.

239
00:27:18.478 --> 00:27:20.478
Is that so?

240
00:27:21.681 --> 00:27:25.334
You must have a strong heart
to play the violin.

241
00:27:25.418 --> 00:27:26.986
Believe me.

242
00:27:27.086 --> 00:27:29.872
And stronger still to live in Vienna.

243
00:27:29.956 --> 00:27:33.842
You shall see.
Vienna is an infuriating city...

244
00:27:33.926 --> 00:27:37.453
infuriating. but magnificent.

245
00:28:34.554 --> 00:28:36.472
Magnificent...

246
00:28:36.556 --> 00:28:38.922
this city!

247
00:28:42.495 --> 00:28:44.495
Antoinette!

248
00:28:45.398 --> 00:28:47.398
May I present to you...

249
00:28:49.402 --> 00:28:51.270
Kaspar Weiss.

250
00:28:51.370 --> 00:28:54.256
One of the most gifted children on earth.

251
00:28:54.340 --> 00:28:56.570
But. Georges. we can't...

252
00:28:57.810 --> 00:29:00.863
My wife. Antoinette Poussin.

253
00:29:00.947 --> 00:29:02.715
Good afternoon. Kaspar.

254
00:29:02.815 --> 00:29:05.634
How nice to meet you.

255
00:29:05.718 --> 00:29:09.905
Go on in. I'll show you
your room in a minute.

256
00:29:09.989 --> 00:29:13.308
Georges. please.
We can't afford to keep him!

257
00:29:13.392 --> 00:29:15.392
We can't afford not to.

258
00:29:18.331 --> 00:29:22.718
There's something about
your playing that eludes me.

259
00:29:22.802 --> 00:29:26.755
I've decided to analyze
it systematically...

260
00:29:26.839 --> 00:29:28.708
with a scientific method.

261
00:29:28.808 --> 00:29:30.543
First...

262
00:29:30.643 --> 00:29:32.111
your bowing...

263
00:29:32.211 --> 00:29:34.329
and your left hand phrasing.

264
00:29:34.413 --> 00:29:38.133
Your détaché.
ornamentation and your taste.

265
00:29:38.217 --> 00:29:39.519
And theory!

266
00:29:39.619 --> 00:29:41.712
Theory. too. is important.

267
00:29:43.022 --> 00:29:47.576
You need a lot more than
inspiration to play the violin.

268
00:29:47.660 --> 00:29:50.754
You need method.
You must think...

269
00:29:51.864 --> 00:29:53.399
and work.

270
00:29:53.499 --> 00:29:55.718
Won't you eat?

271
00:29:55.802 --> 00:29:57.003
You must eat!

272
00:29:57.103 --> 00:29:58.671
Did you want something else?

273
00:29:58.771 --> 00:30:01.657
Try this cheese.
I think you'll like it.

274
00:30:01.741 --> 00:30:03.741
It's French!

275
00:30:04.977 --> 00:30:07.605
-Try some.
-Taste it.

276
00:30:10.349 --> 00:30:15.437
You'll see. a little different
from the monks' crumbly cheese!

277
00:30:15.521 --> 00:30:17.439
Go on!

278
00:30:17.523 --> 00:30:18.458
Kaspar...

279
00:30:18.558 --> 00:30:22.377
if you play well.
you'll enjoy the finest fare.

280
00:30:22.461 --> 00:30:25.080
We can't afford coal. let alone food!

281
00:30:25.164 --> 00:30:27.066
Sell your jewelry!
Sell your David!

282
00:30:27.166 --> 00:30:30.269
Besides he voted
to behead the king. the monster!

283
00:30:30.369 --> 00:30:32.421
My boy...

284
00:30:32.505 --> 00:30:35.991
play well. and there will be cheese.

285
00:30:36.075 --> 00:30:38.873
Violin... cheese.

286
00:30:40.146 --> 00:30:42.064
May I go to my room now?

287
00:30:42.148 --> 00:30:44.241
Go ahead.
And sleep well.

288
00:30:45.318 --> 00:30:48.082
Madame will assist you in your prayers.

289
00:30:52.058 --> 00:30:53.593
Why speak French?

290
00:30:53.693 --> 00:30:57.151
-He doesn't understand.
-So he'll learn!

291
00:30:58.364 --> 00:31:01.265
I want them to know who taught him!

292
00:31:16.449 --> 00:31:18.449
Good morning. Poussin.

293
00:31:19.852 --> 00:31:22.922
I pride myself on visiting
the Taufer Orphanage

294
00:31:23.022 --> 00:31:26.875
three times a year to offer
my services as a teacher.

295
00:31:26.959 --> 00:31:31.246
as a gesture of support
for those good men of the cloth.

296
00:31:31.330 --> 00:31:34.416
This year. they called early.

297
00:31:34.500 --> 00:31:37.419
I was skeptical. but...

298
00:31:37.503 --> 00:31:40.289
when this child raised his bow...

299
00:31:40.373 --> 00:31:45.127
when he played his first note.
well. Baron von Spielmann...

300
00:31:45.211 --> 00:31:47.830
I knew my prayers had been answered.

301
00:31:47.914 --> 00:31:50.906
You've unearthed another Wunderkind.

302
00:31:54.987 --> 00:31:57.139
I've no money for you. Poussin.

303
00:31:57.223 --> 00:31:59.953
I have no concerts to offer you.

304
00:32:01.093 --> 00:32:03.278
It isn't the money.

305
00:32:03.362 --> 00:32:06.148
I suggest you find another patron.

306
00:32:06.232 --> 00:32:08.232
Must I beg?

307
00:32:09.402 --> 00:32:11.587
Isn't that what you're doing?

308
00:32:11.671 --> 00:32:13.671
Yes...

309
00:32:13.906 --> 00:32:15.906
I am.

310
00:32:16.676 --> 00:32:18.827
In three weeks...

311
00:32:18.911 --> 00:32:23.177
I'm holding a private
audition at my salon.

312
00:32:24.216 --> 00:32:26.535
Prince Mannsfeld is leaving...

313
00:32:26.619 --> 00:32:27.787
for Prussia...

314
00:32:27.887 --> 00:32:30.839
and seeks a prodigy to accompany him.

315
00:32:30.923 --> 00:32:32.923
He must hear this boy.

316
00:32:33.492 --> 00:32:36.745
Three weeks.
Can you be ready? Truthfully?

317
00:32:36.829 --> 00:32:38.698
I could be ready tomorrow.

318
00:32:38.798 --> 00:32:41.149
Be very certain. Poussin.

319
00:32:41.233 --> 00:32:43.385
If you embarrass me again...

320
00:32:43.469 --> 00:32:48.023
I've charmed the crowned heads of France.

321
00:32:48.107 --> 00:32:50.626
Where are those heads now?

322
00:32:50.710 --> 00:32:53.720
Rolling in the gutters
of the new Republic!

323
00:33:10.863 --> 00:33:13.181
No. no. no. no!

324
00:33:13.265 --> 00:33:16.018
The first phrase. the entire section.

325
00:33:16.102 --> 00:33:17.803
must be played staccato.

326
00:33:17.903 --> 00:33:22.557
A modern style. well and good.
but let's not be crude.

327
00:33:22.641 --> 00:33:23.825
You liked it. didn't you?

328
00:33:23.909 --> 00:33:26.161
-Yes.
-I'm delighted.

329
00:33:26.245 --> 00:33:29.908
You're going to play it
again and again and again.

330
00:33:39.925 --> 00:33:43.979
See this? It's a clockwork
chronometer. of my invention.

331
00:33:44.063 --> 00:33:46.964
It's called the Poussin-meter.

332
00:33:48.134 --> 00:33:52.002
You will heed it with
the same deference you would me.

333
00:33:53.372 --> 00:33:57.559
What you just played
corresponds to a tempo...

334
00:33:57.643 --> 00:33:59.643
like this.

335
00:34:03.449 --> 00:34:05.867
Each day. as we progress

336
00:34:05.951 --> 00:34:09.671
we shall push down
this little ball one notch.

337
00:34:09.755 --> 00:34:14.317
Until finally. in three weeks.
you'll be playing like this.

338
00:34:18.664 --> 00:34:20.664
The world will be yours.

339
00:34:21.801 --> 00:34:25.581
Antoinette. there's something
I still don't understand.

340
00:34:27.339 --> 00:34:29.992
His violin has a wonderful sound.

341
00:34:30.076 --> 00:34:31.410
and a lovely form.

342
00:34:31.510 --> 00:34:33.595
Of course. it's Italian.

343
00:34:33.679 --> 00:34:36.045
Is it very valuable?

344
00:34:37.583 --> 00:34:39.601
Why do you ask?

345
00:34:39.685 --> 00:34:43.071
Well. we could pay the rent. if ever...

346
00:34:43.155 --> 00:34:46.341
He will play divinely. my dear.

347
00:34:46.425 --> 00:34:48.094
Can't you trust me?

348
00:34:48.194 --> 00:34:50.579
Yes. of course I can.

349
00:34:50.663 --> 00:34:54.449
But must he sleep with it?
He could roll over on it.

350
00:34:54.533 --> 00:34:56.202
What?

351
00:34:56.302 --> 00:34:58.302
He sleeps with it?

352
00:34:58.804 --> 00:35:00.906
Straight. proud.
Lift your chin. There.

353
00:35:01.006 --> 00:35:04.059
Perfect. your bow.
You're clutching.

354
00:35:04.143 --> 00:35:06.941
Your body's stiff. your elbow's locked.

355
00:35:08.280 --> 00:35:10.583
I knew something was holding you back.

356
00:35:10.683 --> 00:35:14.673
Something. but I didn't know what.
Now it's totally clear.

357
00:35:15.688 --> 00:35:20.075
You're oppressed by your violin.
It has you completely enslaved.

358
00:35:20.159 --> 00:35:23.390
Look at you.
There. very good.

359
00:35:25.698 --> 00:35:29.794
If you want to advance.
Kaspar Weiss. you must let go.

360
00:35:30.970 --> 00:35:34.167
What do you mean. sir?
I don't understand.

361
00:35:36.142 --> 00:35:39.475
Antoinette tells me you
sleep with your violin.

362
00:35:40.579 --> 00:35:43.665
Tonight you'll sleep by yourself.

363
00:35:43.749 --> 00:35:45.734
Without the violin.

364
00:35:45.818 --> 00:35:47.818
Without your violin.

365
00:36:00.199 --> 00:36:02.599
Thank you for coming so quickly.

366
00:36:06.872 --> 00:36:09.636
Thank you so much. Doctor.
Good night.

367
00:36:14.880 --> 00:36:16.315
Feeling better?

368
00:36:16.415 --> 00:36:17.950
Yes. thank you.

369
00:36:18.050 --> 00:36:22.771
The doctor says that your heart
must have stopped for a minute.

370
00:36:22.855 --> 00:36:24.190
I'm sorry.

371
00:36:24.290 --> 00:36:28.192
It's all right. but we don't
want it to happen again.

372
00:36:29.762 --> 00:36:32.047
Were you worried?

373
00:36:32.131 --> 00:36:35.851
Were you nervous about the audition?

374
00:36:35.935 --> 00:36:38.053
It will be just fine.

375
00:36:38.137 --> 00:36:40.799
-You know that. don't you?
-Georges!

376
00:36:41.640 --> 00:36:43.209
I know. I know.

377
00:36:43.309 --> 00:36:47.395
Kaspar. we want to tell you.

378
00:36:47.479 --> 00:36:50.866
you don't have to do
it if you don't want to.

379
00:36:50.950 --> 00:36:53.068
You don't have to play.

380
00:36:53.152 --> 00:36:54.854
I don't?

381
00:36:54.954 --> 00:36:57.839
We can cancel the audition.

382
00:36:57.923 --> 00:37:00.118
We'll manage. somehow.

383
00:37:01.660 --> 00:37:04.663
It's better than making
you sick. do you see?

384
00:37:04.763 --> 00:37:07.182
You don't have to be famous.

385
00:37:07.266 --> 00:37:08.734
No?

386
00:37:08.834 --> 00:37:10.834
Yes.

387
00:37:11.103 --> 00:37:12.571
Oui.

388
00:37:12.671 --> 00:37:14.671
I'm sick.

389
00:37:15.774 --> 00:37:19.027
I want to be famous.

390
00:37:19.111 --> 00:37:21.563
Sir. I really do.

391
00:37:21.647 --> 00:37:24.099
That's my boy.

392
00:37:24.183 --> 00:37:26.334
I'm very proud of you.

393
00:37:26.418 --> 00:37:28.537
I want you to rest. relax.

394
00:37:28.621 --> 00:37:30.705
Madame Poussin will bring

395
00:37:30.789 --> 00:37:33.053
a visitor you like very much.

396
00:37:38.397 --> 00:37:40.397
Thank you. madame.

397
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:54.645
Good!

398
00:38:54.606 --> 00:38:56.606
There you go!

399
00:39:30.576 --> 00:39:32.560
We better sleep now.

400
00:39:32.644 --> 00:39:35.477
Tomorrow's going to be a busy day.

401
00:40:09.782 --> 00:40:10.883
Perfect.

402
00:40:10.983 --> 00:40:13.884
And now. backwards.
Are you ready?

403
00:40:53.492 --> 00:40:56.120
Rejected! The shame!

404
00:41:03.302 --> 00:41:05.302
Kaspar Weiss.

405
00:41:05.971 --> 00:41:08.556
Kaspar Weiss. violin!

406
00:41:08.640 --> 00:41:10.592
Play the best you can.

407
00:41:10.676 --> 00:41:12.676
Play your best.

408
00:41:42.608 --> 00:41:47.170
Master Poussin and his
protégé. Kaspar Weiss.

409
00:41:59.424 --> 00:42:01.093
Closer.

410
00:42:01.193 --> 00:42:03.193
Come closer.

411
00:42:06.231 --> 00:42:10.518
So you're the wild
child I've heard all about.

412
00:42:10.602 --> 00:42:13.855
An orphan raised by monks.

413
00:42:13.939 --> 00:42:16.599
If you prefer. we can call in the next.

414
00:42:17.576 --> 00:42:18.710
There's the son of...

415
00:42:18.810 --> 00:42:20.810
No. no.

416
00:42:21.146 --> 00:42:22.648
How charming to think

417
00:42:22.748 --> 00:42:26.401
a monastery has actually
produced something...

418
00:42:26.485 --> 00:42:28.485
something worthwhile.

419
00:42:30.889 --> 00:42:33.409
That's a lovely instrument you have.

420
00:42:34.159 --> 00:42:36.159
May I see it?

421
00:42:36.328 --> 00:42:38.387
May I see it. my boy?

422
00:42:50.342 --> 00:42:52.342
Is it for sale?

423
00:42:53.145 --> 00:42:56.308
I'd give you a good price for it.

424
00:42:57.583 --> 00:43:00.052
He's very attached to his instrument.

425
00:43:00.152 --> 00:43:02.152
So I see.

426
00:43:02.621 --> 00:43:05.840
Perhaps after he's played...

427
00:43:05.924 --> 00:43:09.744
Of course. let him play.
I might take him. too.

428
00:43:09.828 --> 00:43:12.160
Come. play for me.

429
00:43:14.633 --> 00:43:17.932
Won't you play something for me?
Please.

430
00:43:18.637 --> 00:43:20.637
Poussin!

431
00:43:25.410 --> 00:43:27.996
Just play for him. son.

432
00:43:28.080 --> 00:43:30.080
Play.

433
00:45:17.789 --> 00:45:19.789
Monsieur Poussin?

434
00:45:21.593 --> 00:45:24.679
On behalf of the brothers I thank you

435
00:45:24.763 --> 00:45:27.815
for the generosity you showed Kaspar.

436
00:45:27.899 --> 00:45:31.552
He takes with him the
many gifts you gave him.

437
00:45:31.636 --> 00:45:33.721
I did what I could.

438
00:45:33.805 --> 00:45:37.525
Would you honor us
by sharing our modest supper?

439
00:45:37.609 --> 00:45:40.328
It's very kind of you.

440
00:45:40.412 --> 00:45:44.212
but my wife awaits me.
all of Vienna awaits me.

441
00:45:45.317 --> 00:45:48.514
Of course. we understand.

442
00:45:49.621 --> 00:45:51.390
I do have one question.

443
00:45:51.490 --> 00:45:53.325
Yes?

444
00:45:53.425 --> 00:45:55.260
The violin.

445
00:45:55.360 --> 00:45:57.360
Yes?

446
00:45:58.263 --> 00:46:00.561
What will become of it?

447
00:46:01.466 --> 00:46:05.286
I'm sorry. I thought you knew.

448
00:46:05.370 --> 00:46:08.690
Naturally you were
foremost in our thoughts.

449
00:46:08.774 --> 00:46:12.193
After all the time and energy you invested

450
00:46:12.277 --> 00:46:14.395
it would be wrong

451
00:46:14.479 --> 00:46:17.365
to give it to another child.

452
00:46:17.449 --> 00:46:19.051
Yes. of course.

453
00:46:19.151 --> 00:46:21.936
So we buried it with the boy.

454
00:46:22.020 --> 00:46:24.488
He can play it in heaven.

455
00:46:29.861 --> 00:46:31.861
Yes. quite right.

456
00:46:46.745 --> 00:46:51.341
And then I see a time of life.

457
00:46:52.017 --> 00:46:54.769
a time of lust and energy.

458
00:46:54.853 --> 00:47:00.052
loosed across mountains
and oceans and time.

459
00:47:02.894 --> 00:47:05.413
Confusing. madame. I know.

460
00:47:05.497 --> 00:47:07.615
But I see it.

461
00:47:07.699 --> 00:47:09.699
I'm certain.

462
00:47:10.535 --> 00:47:12.765
Yours is a Lazarus soul.

463
00:49:23.835 --> 00:49:25.953
Yes. I see.

464
00:49:26.037 --> 00:49:28.767
Put her through. will you?

465
00:49:30.342 --> 00:49:32.627
We're on hold.

466
00:49:32.711 --> 00:49:36.430
You should tell her our story.
Explain its past.

467
00:49:36.514 --> 00:49:40.151
Brother. please. she doesn't care.
She's doing her job.

468
00:49:40.251 --> 00:49:42.470
But if you convince her...

469
00:49:42.554 --> 00:49:43.722
Father Victor.

470
00:49:43.822 --> 00:49:45.790
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

471
00:49:45.890 --> 00:49:47.025
This is Suzanne.

472
00:49:47.125 --> 00:49:49.127
They're just closing on lot 71.

473
00:49:49.227 --> 00:49:52.613
Can you hear the auctioneer?

474
00:49:52.697 --> 00:49:54.756
Sold to the lady on the left.

475
00:49:55.800 --> 00:49:57.718
Yes. I can hear him.

476
00:49:57.802 --> 00:50:01.455
Suzanne. how do I tell
you when I want to bid?

477
00:50:01.539 --> 00:50:05.459
Leave it to me. sir. Just tell
me when you want to stop.

478
00:50:05.543 --> 00:50:08.113
A masterpiece of the Golden Age.

479
00:50:08.213 --> 00:50:10.315
And. if she will give us the pleasure.

480
00:50:10.415 --> 00:50:13.775
I feel helpless.
Isn't there something we can do?

481
00:50:14.552 --> 00:50:15.954
Yes.

482
00:50:16.054 --> 00:50:17.856
We can pray.

483
00:50:17.956 --> 00:50:19.073
Auctioneer:...interest here. of course.

484
00:50:19.157 --> 00:50:21.275
Last order bid at $250.000.

485
00:50:21.359 --> 00:50:24.729
So. now let's open the floor
and who will start us off?

486
00:50:24.829 --> 00:50:27.882
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

487
00:50:27.966 --> 00:50:30.651
270.000.
Suzanne on the telephone.

488
00:50:30.735 --> 00:50:33.521
280.000.
Back to you. sir.

489
00:50:33.605 --> 00:50:37.245
300.000. I see you. Suzanne.
Against your caller now.

490
00:50:40.512 --> 00:50:42.512
And then...

491
00:50:44.182 --> 00:50:47.268
a man comes into your life...

492
00:50:47.352 --> 00:50:49.403
a handsome man...

493
00:50:49.487 --> 00:50:51.739
and intelligent.

494
00:50:51.823 --> 00:50:54.553
He'll seduce you with his talent

495
00:50:55.460 --> 00:50:57.545
and worse.

496
00:50:57.629 --> 00:50:59.629
In short...

497
00:50:59.798 --> 00:51:01.798
he's the Devil.

498
00:51:30.128 --> 00:51:32.824
What a marvelous violin.

499
00:51:36.234 --> 00:51:37.736
What do you want?

500
00:51:37.836 --> 00:51:40.939
I was lured by the music.
It drew me across the heath.

501
00:51:41.039 --> 00:51:42.307
Oh. yes?

502
00:51:42.407 --> 00:51:44.309
Maybe you can go back the same way.

503
00:51:44.409 --> 00:51:47.606
I'm your host.
This is my land.

504
00:51:48.913 --> 00:51:51.609
Now I see. my mistake.

505
00:51:53.118 --> 00:51:54.753
We will not be a trouble.

506
00:51:54.853 --> 00:51:57.271
We'll be leaving here by nightfall.

507
00:51:57.355 --> 00:51:59.306
That won't be necessary.

508
00:51:59.390 --> 00:52:02.260
I'm sure we can come to some arrangement.

509
00:52:07.665 --> 00:52:08.767
Excuse me. sir?

510
00:52:08.867 --> 00:52:11.185
I must ask you to leave.

511
00:52:11.269 --> 00:52:13.788
We have an invitation.

512
00:52:13.872 --> 00:52:16.724
You can read?

513
00:52:16.808 --> 00:52:19.276
Personal invitation.

514
00:52:36.661 --> 00:52:38.579
-Evening. Percy.
-Good evening. ma'am.

515
00:52:38.663 --> 00:52:40.565
He's in the dressing room. warming up.

516
00:52:40.665 --> 00:52:42.665
Not without me. I hope.

517
00:52:49.340 --> 00:52:52.366
Victoria.

518
00:52:56.714 --> 00:52:58.714
I need you.

519
00:53:03.621 --> 00:53:06.419
I feel a composition coming on.

520
00:53:10.461 --> 00:53:12.461
So do I.

521
00:53:26.377 --> 00:53:28.329
Ladies and gentlemen.

522
00:53:28.413 --> 00:53:30.631
if I can have your attention.

523
00:53:30.715 --> 00:53:33.501
Mr. Pope has asked me to announce

524
00:53:33.585 --> 00:53:36.321
that he will be performing this afternoon

525
00:53:36.421 --> 00:53:38.439
on an antique instrument

526
00:53:38.523 --> 00:53:40.875
of the Italian school.

527
00:53:40.959 --> 00:53:45.055
which has revitalized
his affections for the violin.

528
00:53:53.037 --> 00:53:54.372
I...

529
00:53:54.472 --> 00:53:58.192
hope that whets your appetite

530
00:53:58.276 --> 00:53:59.577
somewhat.

531
00:54:12.090 --> 00:54:14.875
Mr. Pope. sir.
whenever you're...

532
00:54:14.959 --> 00:54:17.860
-Oh. darling.
-ready.

533
00:55:10.815 --> 00:55:13.825
I'd like to play for you
a new composition.

534
00:55:15.653 --> 00:55:18.806
which came to me recently

535
00:55:18.890 --> 00:55:21.809
in a moment of...

536
00:55:21.893 --> 00:55:24.657
inspiration.

537
00:57:32.023 --> 00:57:33.891
'How did it come to this?

538
00:57:33.991 --> 00:57:37.845
Saints in heaven.
how did it happen to him?

539
00:57:37.929 --> 00:57:39.831
An artist who could not be denied.

540
00:57:39.931 --> 00:57:43.550
A poet in fact.
But a murderer.

541
00:57:43.634 --> 00:57:45.634
No.

542
00:57:47.071 --> 00:57:49.774
Yet the looking-glass
image was hard to refute.

543
00:57:49.874 --> 00:57:52.443
His fingers and cuffs
were still ruddy with gore.

544
00:57:52.543 --> 00:57:56.377
And as he watched. in horror...

545
00:57:58.516 --> 00:58:01.586
the speckles of blood seemed
to multiply before his eyes

546
00:58:01.686 --> 00:58:05.939
like maggots on a fetid corpse.

547
00:58:06.023 --> 00:58:07.959
And what would become of him now?

548
00:58:08.059 --> 00:58:11.478
Where would he run to
and where would he hide?

549
00:58:11.562 --> 00:58:13.965
The options just then
were depressingly few.

550
00:58:14.065 --> 00:58:17.484
Indeed his mind was already racing east

551
00:58:17.568 --> 00:58:19.871
- across the frozen continent... '
- Darling.

552
00:58:19.971 --> 00:58:22.006
'and over the frozen steppes... '

553
00:58:22.106 --> 00:58:23.241
Darling.

554
00:58:23.341 --> 00:58:26.377
'back to the refuge of
his childhood estate.'

555
00:58:26.477 --> 00:58:28.413
I have a theme I want to work out.

556
00:58:28.513 --> 00:58:31.048
"To Russia. ' he heard the Cossack call.'

557
00:58:31.148 --> 00:58:33.100
It needs to be addressed.

558
00:58:33.184 --> 00:58:35.494
Can't you see I'm trying to work?

559
00:58:40.024 --> 00:58:41.225
You're so selfish.

560
00:58:41.325 --> 00:58:43.694
It was mutual inspiration I had in mind.

561
00:58:43.794 --> 00:58:46.079
Can't you see I don't need any?
I was writing here like...

562
00:58:46.163 --> 00:58:47.999
My love. don't be angry.

563
00:58:48.099 --> 00:58:51.418
-Oh. please.
-You've only yourself to blame.

564
00:58:51.502 --> 00:58:54.302
It's your beauty that summons the music.

565
00:58:57.642 --> 00:59:00.060
And when it comes...

566
00:59:00.144 --> 00:59:02.442
I must play.

567
00:59:06.684 --> 00:59:08.684
Damn you.

568
00:59:48.459 --> 00:59:50.484
Is this what you wanted?

569
00:59:52.496 --> 00:59:54.496
Is this what you wanted?

570
01:00:40.778 --> 01:00:44.932
'East... east across the frozen continent

571
01:00:45.016 --> 01:00:47.100
and over the frozen steppes.

572
01:00:47.184 --> 01:00:50.771
back to the refuge of
his childhood estate.

573
01:00:50.855 --> 01:00:52.356
'To Russia...

574
01:00:52.456 --> 01:00:56.243
to Russia. ' he heard the Cossack call.'

575
01:00:56.327 --> 01:00:59.880
-Frederick.
-My darling.

576
01:00:59.964 --> 01:01:02.983
My one inspiration.

577
01:01:03.067 --> 01:01:05.136
I have something terrible to tell you.

578
01:01:05.236 --> 01:01:07.721
Terrible?

579
01:01:07.805 --> 01:01:09.373
The worst.

580
01:01:09.473 --> 01:01:12.243
It must be most terrible
for you to tell me now

581
01:01:12.343 --> 01:01:15.210
and ruin this perfect moment.

582
01:01:16.681 --> 01:01:19.115
Jack has killed the minister.

583
01:01:20.418 --> 01:01:22.369
It was an accident.

584
01:01:22.453 --> 01:01:24.453
I see.

585
01:01:25.690 --> 01:01:28.108
He's now fled to Russia.

586
01:01:28.192 --> 01:01:30.192
Self-imposed exile.

587
01:01:32.063 --> 01:01:34.381
I see.

588
01:01:34.465 --> 01:01:36.465
You're leaving me.

589
01:01:38.202 --> 01:01:40.153
I've never been there

590
01:01:40.237 --> 01:01:42.173
and I don't know what to write

591
01:01:42.273 --> 01:01:45.376
-I have to follow him.
-I can't go. I've concerts.

592
01:01:45.476 --> 01:01:47.476
I know. darling.

593
01:01:50.414 --> 01:01:52.733
Are you very angry?

594
01:01:52.817 --> 01:01:54.817
Why should I be?

595
01:02:25.249 --> 01:02:27.818
'Dearest Frederick.
I've just passed the church

596
01:02:27.918 --> 01:02:30.003
near Charrington.
where Jeffrey was baptized

597
01:02:30.087 --> 01:02:32.472
and I'm quickly approaching
the Rutherford bridge.

598
01:02:32.556 --> 01:02:33.624
In other words.

599
01:02:33.724 --> 01:02:34.959
darling.

600
01:02:35.059 --> 01:02:36.994
we have parted for under 10 minutes

601
01:02:37.094 --> 01:02:39.646
and already I'm lost.

602
01:02:39.730 --> 01:02:41.682
I return to my writing

603
01:02:41.766 --> 01:02:44.651
in the hope that these few honest words

604
01:02:44.735 --> 01:02:47.538
- might rejoin our lips...'
- 'Darling Victoria. '

605
01:02:47.638 --> 01:02:50.608
'...bring back your hands
to my shivering skin.'

606
01:02:50.708 --> 01:02:52.592
'You trust in words
in the comfort of letters

607
01:02:52.676 --> 01:02:54.445
in a way that I simply do not.

608
01:02:54.545 --> 01:02:57.682
And no matter the language.
no words can convince me

609
01:02:57.782 --> 01:02:59.900
- that you are not gone... '
- 'Frederick. my love.

610
01:02:59.984 --> 01:03:01.935
it's Moscow at last
and my very first night

611
01:03:02.019 --> 01:03:04.004
was unspeakably dreary.

612
01:03:04.088 --> 01:03:07.040
Can any one nation
be quite so abysmal... '

613
01:03:07.124 --> 01:03:09.409
- 'What is this nonsense? '
- 'Or is it just simply

614
01:03:09.493 --> 01:03:11.445
- that you are not here? '
- 'Do not expect me

615
01:03:11.529 --> 01:03:13.264
to sigh for your woes.

616
01:03:13.364 --> 01:03:16.567
If everything truly is as it is
more than you say.

617
01:03:16.667 --> 01:03:18.885
- then heed my simple remedy.'
- 'Frederick... '

618
01:03:18.969 --> 01:03:20.971
- 'Return at once... '
- 'darling.

619
01:03:21.071 --> 01:03:23.090
I long for your touch.

620
01:03:23.174 --> 01:03:25.124
I still seek your scent on my clothes.'

621
01:03:25.209 --> 01:03:27.761
'Come to me now.
I will free you.

622
01:03:27.845 --> 01:03:29.796
I should have pinned you to the mattress

623
01:03:29.880 --> 01:03:33.084
when last I had the chance.
Like you were the butterfly.

624
01:03:33.184 --> 01:03:35.135
I was the pin.'

625
01:03:35.219 --> 01:03:38.322
'...embroidered together.
heart against heart.'

626
01:03:38.422 --> 01:03:40.373
'Victoria. listen.

627
01:03:40.457 --> 01:03:42.709
our moment is dying...
What is this nonsense...?

628
01:03:42.793 --> 01:03:44.778
The music has come...
Like you were the butterfly...

629
01:03:44.862 --> 01:03:48.648
Everything precious is passing. my love...

630
01:03:48.732 --> 01:03:51.718
For everything I said to you

631
01:03:51.802 --> 01:03:53.920
and everything I might ever say
could be contained

632
01:03:54.004 --> 01:03:57.624
in these two words...

633
01:03:57.708 --> 01:04:00.093
come back. Victoria.

634
01:04:00.177 --> 01:04:02.195
Come back.'

635
01:04:02.279 --> 01:04:05.737
Do not write to me anymore. love.

636
01:04:29.506 --> 01:04:32.225
Ladies and gentlemen.

637
01:04:32.309 --> 01:04:35.829
thank you for your
patience and understanding.

638
01:04:35.913 --> 01:04:37.748
Unfortunately.

639
01:04:37.848 --> 01:04:40.066
I have just received notice

640
01:04:40.150 --> 01:04:43.670
that Mr. Pope has been...

641
01:04:43.754 --> 01:04:46.245
afflicted by an illness.

642
01:04:48.058 --> 01:04:50.010
and unfortunately.

643
01:04:50.094 --> 01:04:52.846
cannot be with us today.

644
01:04:52.930 --> 01:04:56.583
Of course. we will
refund those who desire.

645
01:04:56.667 --> 01:04:59.119
but for those who do stay.

646
01:04:59.203 --> 01:05:01.539
we are pleased to play my arrangement

647
01:05:01.639 --> 01:05:05.405
of favorite English madrigals.

648
01:05:22.760 --> 01:05:26.179
'Darling Frederick.
I have seen the truth at last.

649
01:05:26.263 --> 01:05:28.833
Eternity has passed since we were parted.

650
01:05:28.933 --> 01:05:30.868
One full week without your letters

651
01:05:30.968 --> 01:05:33.571
and I am shriveling here
like a flower in the desert.

652
01:05:33.671 --> 01:05:36.089
I will not suffer more.

653
01:05:36.173 --> 01:05:38.275
I'm not reading. as well as not writing

654
01:05:38.375 --> 01:05:40.678
and you'll miss this crucial report.

655
01:05:40.778 --> 01:05:42.696
I'm coming back. my love.

656
01:05:42.780 --> 01:05:45.950
by any means I can.
tomorrow morning if I'm able.

657
01:05:46.050 --> 01:05:48.969
And then. will you forgive me. my love?

658
01:05:49.053 --> 01:05:52.239
The wasted time. my selfish folly.

659
01:05:52.323 --> 01:05:54.425
Will you take me in your arms again?

660
01:05:54.525 --> 01:05:56.476
And with one kiss eradicate

661
01:05:56.560 --> 01:05:59.324
each hour apart from your embrace.

662
01:06:03.033 --> 01:06:05.352
I long for you. love.

663
01:06:05.436 --> 01:06:09.289
I long for your touch and constant heart.

664
01:06:09.373 --> 01:06:11.373
Victoria.'

665
01:07:12.503 --> 01:07:14.204
Savage!

666
01:07:14.304 --> 01:07:16.456
Extreme. rude. cruel.

667
01:07:16.540 --> 01:07:19.592
-Oh. not to trust.
-Victoria.

668
01:07:19.676 --> 01:07:21.478
-You sluttish muse.
-Who is she?

669
01:07:21.578 --> 01:07:23.414
-Quiet!
-Victoria. please.

670
01:07:23.514 --> 01:07:25.532
Don't try to explain.

671
01:07:25.616 --> 01:07:27.634
It's not your fault.

672
01:07:27.718 --> 01:07:29.718
Or yours.

673
01:07:30.421 --> 01:07:33.322
Victoria.
Listen.

674
01:07:46.737 --> 01:07:48.922
'Do not despair. Victoria.

675
01:07:49.006 --> 01:07:52.258
This is the last page
of our correspondence.

676
01:07:52.342 --> 01:07:55.879
I'm only writing to let you know
of my plans for suicide.

677
01:07:55.979 --> 01:07:59.632
by poison or drowning.
I have yet to decide.

678
01:07:59.716 --> 01:08:02.369
All my estate I'm leaving to you.

679
01:08:02.453 --> 01:08:05.189
I have some personal debts
that I intend to honor

680
01:08:05.289 --> 01:08:07.992
but everything else
will be yours to dispose of.

681
01:08:08.092 --> 01:08:10.276
Do with it what you will.

682
01:08:10.360 --> 01:08:12.360
It matters little to me.

683
01:08:13.263 --> 01:08:15.315
Regretfully yours.

684
01:08:15.399 --> 01:08:16.800
Frederick.'

685
01:08:16.900 --> 01:08:18.900
I'm dying.

686
01:08:19.570 --> 01:08:21.438
I'm dying.

687
01:08:21.538 --> 01:08:23.440
Do you know anything about music?

688
01:08:23.540 --> 01:08:25.458
Have you heard of Frederick Pope?
Lord Frederick Pope.

689
01:08:25.542 --> 01:08:27.177
composer. genius.

690
01:08:27.277 --> 01:08:29.980
The only goddamn virtuoso
that the nation of England

691
01:08:30.080 --> 01:08:31.815
ever came up with.

692
01:08:31.915 --> 01:08:35.035
In a few minutes.
his violin is gonna be sold

693
01:08:35.119 --> 01:08:37.103
and if I don't get there
because of your driving

694
01:08:37.187 --> 01:08:39.139
or this goddamn traffic.

695
01:08:39.223 --> 01:08:41.174
I'm going to lose my precious testicles.

696
01:08:41.258 --> 01:08:44.577
Do you understand?
I'm going to be castrated.

697
01:08:44.661 --> 01:08:47.414
Please hurry.

698
01:08:47.498 --> 01:08:49.523
It's there. Duval's.

699
01:08:49.967 --> 01:08:52.318
That's it?

700
01:08:52.402 --> 01:08:55.522
Why didn't you tell me?

701
01:08:55.606 --> 01:08:57.606
I need a receipt.

702
01:08:59.009 --> 01:09:01.361
Hello.
Nicholas Olsberg.

703
01:09:01.445 --> 01:09:03.863
-I'm late.
-Yes. you are.

704
01:09:03.947 --> 01:09:06.187
Please don't let me forget this.

705
01:09:06.950 --> 01:09:09.402
Olsberg. Nicholas.

706
01:09:09.486 --> 01:09:12.138
I registered by telephone.

707
01:09:12.222 --> 01:09:14.874
Check again under Pope Foundation.

708
01:09:14.958 --> 01:09:16.958
Pope.

709
01:09:17.761 --> 01:09:20.097
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti...

710
01:09:20.197 --> 01:09:22.647
Here we are.
Please sign.

711
01:09:26.336 --> 01:09:28.172
There you are.

712
01:09:28.272 --> 01:09:30.857
Here she is now. lot number 72.

713
01:09:30.941 --> 01:09:34.160
the so-called Red Violin.

714
01:09:34.244 --> 01:09:37.363
The last order bid is at $250.000.

715
01:09:37.447 --> 01:09:40.900
So we'll open the floor
and who will start us off?

716
01:09:40.984 --> 01:09:43.320
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

717
01:09:43.420 --> 01:09:45.355
270.000.
Suzanne here on the telephone.

718
01:09:45.455 --> 01:09:46.990
280.000.
Back to you. sir.

719
01:09:47.090 --> 01:09:49.526
300.000 at the back of the room.
thank you.

720
01:09:49.626 --> 01:09:51.911
320.000.
Suzanne. I see you.

721
01:09:51.995 --> 01:09:55.522
400.000 at the back of the hall.
400.000...

722
01:13:35.419 --> 01:13:37.478
Darling. come here.

723
01:13:42.125 --> 01:13:44.125
Do you like it?

724
01:13:51.768 --> 01:13:53.768
Justice...

725
01:13:56.206 --> 01:13:58.157
There will be a trial.

726
01:13:58.241 --> 01:14:00.560
A great trial...

727
01:14:00.644 --> 01:14:03.563
before a powerful magistrate.

728
01:14:03.647 --> 01:14:05.774
And you... you will be guilty.

729
01:14:07.284 --> 01:14:09.086
Beware!

730
01:14:09.186 --> 01:14:11.186
Beware the heat of the fire!

731
01:15:18.288 --> 01:15:22.742
Comrade Chan Gong has come from Beijing.

732
01:15:22.826 --> 01:15:25.693
Welcome her. please.

733
01:15:39.109 --> 01:15:41.027
Comrades. students.

734
01:15:41.111 --> 01:15:44.063
revolutionary companions-in-arms...

735
01:15:44.147 --> 01:15:48.880
I give you my proletarian salute.

736
01:15:54.658 --> 01:15:57.743
I congratulate you on
today's grand festival

737
01:15:57.827 --> 01:16:00.580
for which you have worked so hard.

738
01:16:00.664 --> 01:16:04.225
Your cultural unit has
done exceptional work.

739
01:16:09.072 --> 01:16:14.660
I would also commend you
on the children's presentation.

740
01:16:14.744 --> 01:16:17.864
It made my heart rejoice.

741
01:16:17.948 --> 01:16:20.317
The story of 'The Three Heroic Girls'

742
01:16:20.417 --> 01:16:22.468
was a vivid lesson.

743
01:16:22.552 --> 01:16:27.306
It galvanized our historic crusade!

744
01:16:27.390 --> 01:16:31.711
But unfortunately. some efforts

745
01:16:31.795 --> 01:16:34.286
are less successful.

746
01:16:36.299 --> 01:16:39.519
Sometimes the teacher must learn

747
01:16:39.603 --> 01:16:41.764
from his students.

748
01:16:45.508 --> 01:16:47.508
Give it to me.

749
01:16:54.951 --> 01:16:58.871
Capitalist exploitation
survived for centuries

750
01:16:58.955 --> 01:17:01.541
yet its 'classics' are pitiful.

751
01:17:01.625 --> 01:17:06.345
Foreign music is meaningless and empty.

752
01:17:06.429 --> 01:17:09.065
What do they mean by
'symphony. ' 'concerto. '

753
01:17:09.165 --> 01:17:11.817
'No 1.' 'No 2.' 'No 3'?

754
01:17:11.901 --> 01:17:15.639
This is empty formalism.
It speaks nothing to the people.

755
01:17:15.739 --> 01:17:18.891
What good is making music

756
01:17:18.975 --> 01:17:23.362
except to teach and inspire the people?

757
01:17:23.446 --> 01:17:25.505
Long live Chairman Mao!

758
01:17:27.317 --> 01:17:29.907
Overthrow the cultural establishment!

759
01:17:33.890 --> 01:17:34.758
Chou Yuan?

760
01:17:34.858 --> 01:17:35.825
Present.

761
01:17:35.925 --> 01:17:38.587
Why do you teach this instrument?

762
01:17:42.032 --> 01:17:45.151
Comrade Chan Gong. what you say is true...

763
01:17:45.235 --> 01:17:47.235
Louder. please.

764
01:17:49.839 --> 01:17:52.825
Comrade Chan Gong. you are right.

765
01:17:52.909 --> 01:17:55.094
Much of Western music

766
01:17:55.178 --> 01:17:57.096
is unrefined. worthless.

767
01:17:57.180 --> 01:17:59.632
This is a fact.

768
01:17:59.716 --> 01:18:04.103
Everything you said is true.
but the music I teach...

769
01:18:04.187 --> 01:18:05.889
Go on!

770
01:18:05.989 --> 01:18:09.008
The music I teach is
revolutionary music...

771
01:18:09.092 --> 01:18:11.243
Beethoven. Prokofiev...

772
01:18:11.327 --> 01:18:13.327
Do you think so?

773
01:18:13.897 --> 01:18:16.182
In his speech. Comrade Li said...

774
01:18:16.266 --> 01:18:19.418
Comrade Li was purged and humiliated.

775
01:18:19.502 --> 01:18:21.502
Do you wish to quote him?

776
01:18:22.872 --> 01:18:26.359
I didn't know.

777
01:18:26.443 --> 01:18:28.928
I have taught for many years.

778
01:18:29.012 --> 01:18:30.714
That is apparent.

779
01:18:30.814 --> 01:18:33.733
We believe in the rule of many voices.

780
01:18:33.817 --> 01:18:35.685
What should we do here?

781
01:18:35.785 --> 01:18:38.037
Throw away that old junk!

782
01:18:38.121 --> 01:18:40.673
Chou Yuan you must admit your guilt.

783
01:18:40.757 --> 01:18:43.487
Let's challenge degenerate Western art!

784
01:18:44.227 --> 01:18:46.821
Comrade. may I say a few words?

785
01:18:49.432 --> 01:18:51.432
Of course.

786
01:18:52.569 --> 01:18:57.006
Students. comrades.
revolutionary Red Guards...

787
01:18:58.575 --> 01:19:02.161
I'm not an authority on foreign music.

788
01:19:02.245 --> 01:19:04.814
I have not studied like Comrade Chan Gong.

789
01:19:04.914 --> 01:19:07.133
But in my opinion

790
01:19:07.217 --> 01:19:10.927
there's nothing as beautiful
as our traditional music.

791
01:19:11.621 --> 01:19:14.071
Chou Yuan also teaches the hu chin.

792
01:19:14.891 --> 01:19:16.891
Could he not focus on that?

793
01:19:25.034 --> 01:19:27.798
Comrade Xiang has shown her wisdom.

794
01:19:34.911 --> 01:19:39.678
Put this down with the other 'great olds'!

795
01:19:48.458 --> 01:19:51.677
To every problem there is a solution!

796
01:19:51.761 --> 01:19:54.513
I'm sure you can discover the problems.

797
01:19:54.597 --> 01:19:57.464
And I'm sure that you can solve them.

798
01:22:53.509 --> 01:22:55.509
Who's there?

799
01:22:55.711 --> 01:22:57.711
Who is it?

800
01:22:58.281 --> 01:23:00.875
Who's there?

801
01:23:03.619 --> 01:23:05.087
Ming!

802
01:23:05.187 --> 01:23:07.451
You scared me.
I didn't hear you.

803
01:23:16.866 --> 01:23:19.284
It's a mess.
I was tidying up.

804
01:23:19.368 --> 01:23:21.529
What's that?

805
01:23:24.173 --> 01:23:26.173
This is a violin...

806
01:23:27.143 --> 01:23:29.428
a musical instrument from Europe.

807
01:23:29.512 --> 01:23:30.913
-From Europe?
-Yes.

808
01:23:31.013 --> 01:23:32.248
Is it a bad thing?

809
01:23:32.348 --> 01:23:36.935
No. A violin itself is a good thing.

810
01:23:37.019 --> 01:23:39.681
Here. Take a look.

811
01:23:43.159 --> 01:23:46.329
We have to study foreign music
so we can move on

812
01:23:46.429 --> 01:23:48.413
as Chairman Mao said.

813
01:23:48.497 --> 01:23:50.549
Dad asked if you're coming.

814
01:23:50.633 --> 01:23:52.168
He's waiting.

815
01:23:52.268 --> 01:23:55.520
Yes. Tell him I'll come
to see him right away.

816
01:23:55.604 --> 01:23:57.774
As soon as I finish my... work.

817
01:24:01.277 --> 01:24:04.371
-Ming?
-Yes?

818
01:24:05.681 --> 01:24:10.983
What you see here... don't tell anyone.

819
01:24:17.059 --> 01:24:19.059
I want you to listen.

820
01:25:13.349 --> 01:25:15.729
This will be our secret. all right?

821
01:25:20.756 --> 01:25:22.756
Go.

822
01:25:47.817 --> 01:25:49.817
Ming!

823
01:25:52.288 --> 01:25:54.206
-Was she home?
-Yes.

824
01:25:54.290 --> 01:25:58.410
-Is she coming?
-No. She said she'd meet you.

825
01:25:58.494 --> 01:26:00.545
What? Is she coming or not?

826
01:26:00.629 --> 01:26:03.181
-I can't say why.
-Why what?

827
01:26:03.265 --> 01:26:05.401
I promised her to keep it secret.

828
01:26:05.501 --> 01:26:07.503
What are you saying?
I'm your father.

829
01:26:07.603 --> 01:26:10.333
You must tell me everything.

830
01:26:17.580 --> 01:26:19.115
-Xiang Pei!
-Papa. don't!

831
01:26:19.215 --> 01:26:22.267
Open up. It's me.

832
01:26:22.351 --> 01:26:24.536
Where's the key?

833
01:26:24.620 --> 01:26:26.620
Go!

834
01:26:35.831 --> 01:26:37.831
Quiet!

835
01:26:46.642 --> 01:26:48.642
Where is she?

836
01:26:53.549 --> 01:26:55.549
Water! Water!

837
01:27:08.797 --> 01:27:10.797
She's gone!

838
01:27:47.536 --> 01:27:49.536
Is this her?

839
01:27:55.477 --> 01:27:59.538
Look at the date: 1937.
It must be her mother.

840
01:28:21.003 --> 01:28:23.003
Chou Yuan!

841
01:28:23.238 --> 01:28:25.238
Chou Yuan!

842
01:28:26.542 --> 01:28:28.542
Chou Yuan!

843
01:28:36.885 --> 01:28:38.737
-What do you want?
-Please let me in.

844
01:28:38.821 --> 01:28:40.589
I've done nothing.

845
01:28:40.689 --> 01:28:42.689
Let me inside.

846
01:28:56.005 --> 01:28:59.497
-This is for you.
-I don't want it.

847
01:29:09.385 --> 01:29:11.979
It's for you. Take it.

848
01:29:13.889 --> 01:29:15.889
It's a violin.

849
01:29:16.425 --> 01:29:19.792
-A violin.
-I remember.

850
01:29:22.231 --> 01:29:24.583
Do you want it or not?

851
01:29:24.667 --> 01:29:26.936
I'm an old man. but I'm not a fool.

852
01:29:27.036 --> 01:29:29.988
Where are your comrades?

853
01:29:30.072 --> 01:29:32.290
Are they waiting outside?

854
01:29:32.374 --> 01:29:33.976
This isn't a trap.

855
01:29:34.076 --> 01:29:35.177
I've changed.

856
01:29:35.277 --> 01:29:38.296
I don't need it now.
I speak from my heart.

857
01:29:38.380 --> 01:29:40.380
Enough!

858
01:29:42.051 --> 01:29:45.337
And I don't need this.

859
01:29:45.421 --> 01:29:49.207
It's from another time.

860
01:29:49.291 --> 01:29:52.510
If you want it. you can have it

861
01:29:52.594 --> 01:29:55.324
or else no one will.

862
01:29:57.433 --> 01:29:59.697
Do you want it or not?

863
01:30:02.504 --> 01:30:04.504
I've no time!

864
01:30:05.574 --> 01:30:07.701
No more arguments.

865
01:30:10.379 --> 01:30:12.609
Take it!

866
01:30:15.017 --> 01:30:19.037
I am a cadre in the Party.
Do you understand?

867
01:30:19.121 --> 01:30:21.773
I can't keep it.

868
01:30:21.857 --> 01:30:25.987
I love the people.
Do you understand?

869
01:30:41.210 --> 01:30:43.210
Xiang Pei!

870
01:30:46.381 --> 01:30:48.440
I will keep it safe.

871
01:30:57.693 --> 01:31:00.145
Let's go eat.
I'm starving.

872
01:31:00.229 --> 01:31:04.825
Go ahead. I'll wait here.
I'm sure she'll be back.

873
01:31:26.054 --> 01:31:28.640
Auctioneer:...$1.950.000.

874
01:31:28.724 --> 01:31:32.577
And sold to the lady on my left.

875
01:31:32.661 --> 01:31:35.980
The last sale of the evening.
lot number 72.

876
01:31:36.064 --> 01:31:39.134
on the turntable there.
The star of the night...

877
01:31:39.234 --> 01:31:40.569
where is she?

878
01:31:40.669 --> 01:31:44.989
The last violin of Niccolò Bussotti. 1681.

879
01:31:45.073 --> 01:31:47.342
-A masterpiece of the...
-Do you see it?

880
01:31:47.442 --> 01:31:48.644
No. not yet.

881
01:31:48.744 --> 01:31:51.054
If she will give us the pleasure.

882
01:31:52.381 --> 01:31:55.166
And here she is now. lot number 72.

883
01:31:55.250 --> 01:31:58.136
the so-called Red Violin.

884
01:31:58.220 --> 01:32:02.273
-And the last order bid...
-Not at all how I remember it.

885
01:32:02.357 --> 01:32:04.993
They've cleaned it up
and fixed it. It's better.

886
01:32:05.093 --> 01:32:08.146
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

887
01:32:08.230 --> 01:32:10.032
270.000.
Suzanne on the telephones.

888
01:32:10.132 --> 01:32:13.202
-Maybe if I heard it again.
-280.000. Back to you. sir.

889
01:32:13.302 --> 01:32:14.970
300.000 at the back of the hall.

890
01:32:15.070 --> 01:32:16.939
320.000.
Suzanne. I see you.

891
01:32:17.039 --> 01:32:18.674
340.000.
I have you here.

892
01:32:18.774 --> 01:32:21.994
-380.000. Mr. Ruselsky.
-The last card.

893
01:32:23.445 --> 01:32:25.445
The last card.

894
01:32:33.222 --> 01:32:36.407
-Oh. my God!
-Courage. madame.

895
01:32:36.491 --> 01:32:38.360
Upside down.

896
01:32:38.460 --> 01:32:41.079
At this point in the spread

897
01:32:41.163 --> 01:32:43.654
it might be good news.

898
01:32:46.468 --> 01:32:48.468
I feel...

899
01:32:48.971 --> 01:32:52.557
I feel the fast air sweeping around you...

900
01:32:52.641 --> 01:32:55.160
carrying you...

901
01:32:55.244 --> 01:32:57.962
furious wind...

902
01:32:58.046 --> 01:33:00.046
and then stopping.

903
01:33:07.489 --> 01:33:12.243
Your journey will end.
No question. I see it.

904
01:33:12.327 --> 01:33:16.696
One way or another. your travels are over.

905
01:33:19.434 --> 01:33:23.087
And there is trouble in this...

906
01:33:23.171 --> 01:33:25.171
like always.

907
01:33:27.576 --> 01:33:29.278
But you...

908
01:33:29.378 --> 01:33:31.596
you are strong by now...

909
01:33:31.680 --> 01:33:35.133
strong like a tree in the forest.

910
01:33:35.217 --> 01:33:37.502
Where is he?

911
01:33:37.586 --> 01:33:39.586
Upstairs.

912
01:33:46.361 --> 01:33:48.096
You are not alone.

913
01:33:48.196 --> 01:33:52.717
A crowd of faces. friends and family.

914
01:33:52.801 --> 01:33:55.720
enemies. lovers.

915
01:33:55.804 --> 01:33:59.424
You will attract many admirers

916
01:33:59.508 --> 01:34:01.874
fighting to win your hand.

917
01:34:03.345 --> 01:34:04.813
And money...

918
01:34:04.913 --> 01:34:06.998
lots of money.

919
01:34:07.082 --> 01:34:08.951
No. madame.

920
01:34:09.051 --> 01:34:11.703
Don't be afraid.

921
01:34:11.787 --> 01:34:14.606
In this card I see...

922
01:34:14.690 --> 01:34:17.742
I see...

923
01:34:17.826 --> 01:34:20.659
a rebirth.

924
01:34:22.030 --> 01:34:24.933
-And how was your flight?
-Very good. On time.

925
01:34:25.033 --> 01:34:26.969
Sorry to cut your holiday short.

926
01:34:27.069 --> 01:34:29.020
It's quite all right.
I'm excited actually.

927
01:34:29.104 --> 01:34:31.055
-Like Christmas.
-It won't take too long.

928
01:34:31.139 --> 01:34:33.291
We already divided them
up and assessed them.

929
01:34:33.375 --> 01:34:34.993
-Right. Ballpark.
-And all that they want

930
01:34:35.077 --> 01:34:36.979
-is for you to confirm it.
-I got it.

931
01:34:37.079 --> 01:34:38.013
A second opinion.

932
01:34:38.113 --> 01:34:40.048
I've done this sort of thing before.

933
01:34:40.148 --> 01:34:42.248
Can't wait to see it. actually.

934
01:34:44.286 --> 01:34:46.386
This is Mr. Morritz.
You know...

935
01:34:48.824 --> 01:34:50.525
So. you're the expert?

936
01:34:50.625 --> 01:34:53.011
From New York.

937
01:34:53.095 --> 01:34:55.446
Do you know what you're doing?

938
01:34:55.530 --> 01:34:57.199
Yes. New York.

939
01:34:57.299 --> 01:34:58.716
Do you know what you're doing?

940
01:34:58.800 --> 01:34:59.701
Oh.

941
01:34:59.801 --> 01:35:02.253
Why yes.
I certainly hope so.

942
01:35:02.337 --> 01:35:04.622
These people from Duval's
have given us some figures

943
01:35:04.706 --> 01:35:08.493
and we have figures from
the government of China.

944
01:35:08.577 --> 01:35:10.495
What we need now is...

945
01:35:10.579 --> 01:35:12.530
Professional opinion.

946
01:35:12.614 --> 01:35:14.565
No. a signed affidavit.

947
01:35:14.649 --> 01:35:16.601
That's what I'm here for.

948
01:35:16.685 --> 01:35:18.703
Show me to the Strad.

949
01:35:18.787 --> 01:35:21.623
-They all look the same to me.
-But they're not.

950
01:35:21.723 --> 01:35:23.592
Please don't let me forget this.

951
01:35:23.692 --> 01:35:25.717
Over there.

952
01:35:32.501 --> 01:35:34.886
Here she is.

953
01:35:34.970 --> 01:35:36.970
It's a beautiful specimen.

954
01:35:40.242 --> 01:35:42.627
I'd say about...

955
01:35:42.711 --> 01:35:45.930
1683.

956
01:35:46.014 --> 01:35:47.549
Reminds me of the Cobet.

957
01:35:47.649 --> 01:35:49.799
These are the best
quality pieces we found.

958
01:35:49.885 --> 01:35:51.053
And here...

959
01:35:51.153 --> 01:35:53.755
over here. if you'd like to take a look.

960
01:35:53.855 --> 01:35:55.405
are the less promising entries.

961
01:35:55.490 --> 01:35:57.490
Some of them are pretty bad.

962
01:35:59.995 --> 01:36:02.447
So I see.

963
01:36:02.531 --> 01:36:04.166
I guess I'll leave it to you.

964
01:36:04.266 --> 01:36:08.486
I've taken care of the luggage.
I have a driver waiting.

965
01:36:08.570 --> 01:36:10.570
I shouldn't be long.

966
01:36:43.572 --> 01:36:45.707
-Bonjour.
-Bonjour. Mr. Morritz.

967
01:36:45.807 --> 01:36:48.026
Everything is ready as
you asked for. I hope.

968
01:36:48.110 --> 01:36:50.294
-Same room as always?
-We have the same room

969
01:36:50.378 --> 01:36:52.047
but one story down.

970
01:36:52.147 --> 01:36:54.098
If it's not the same floor.
it's not the same room. is it?

971
01:36:54.182 --> 01:36:56.518
No. sir. But it's the
same as the other one.

972
01:36:56.618 --> 01:36:59.437
Oh. sir. I have a message from your wife.

973
01:36:59.521 --> 01:37:01.521
Merci.

974
01:37:11.766 --> 01:37:14.419
Room 2703.

975
01:37:14.503 --> 01:37:16.562
New York City. please.

976
01:37:17.672 --> 01:37:20.368
316-2799.

977
01:37:23.945 --> 01:37:26.264
Carrie. Charles Morritz here.

978
01:37:26.348 --> 01:37:29.451
I have a little gumshoe work
I need you to get onto.

979
01:37:29.551 --> 01:37:31.702
Cremona. Bussotti.

980
01:37:31.786 --> 01:37:33.786
Get a pen.

981
01:37:39.194 --> 01:37:42.204
Made a cast of this
after we set the table.

982
01:37:43.598 --> 01:37:45.333
The Swiss...

983
01:37:45.433 --> 01:37:46.501
so here we are.

984
01:37:46.601 --> 01:37:48.786
Here's the before picture.

985
01:37:48.870 --> 01:37:50.088
Take a look at the corners.

986
01:37:50.172 --> 01:37:52.457
Not too bad. I don't think
we have to touch them.

987
01:37:52.541 --> 01:37:54.907
Some really nice purfling here.

988
01:37:56.878 --> 01:37:58.713
A lot of work to get it this far.

989
01:37:58.813 --> 01:38:01.065
Turn-of-the-century hack job
with some horse glue

990
01:38:01.149 --> 01:38:03.285
and a patch. so I had to reset the neck.

991
01:38:03.385 --> 01:38:06.671
That was the big job.
Sound post. tailpiece.

992
01:38:06.755 --> 01:38:08.924
new bridge. of course.
But the body itself

993
01:38:09.024 --> 01:38:11.893
is remarkably good.
I'm just gonna clean it up.

994
01:38:11.993 --> 01:38:15.012
-strip back some varnish...
-No. no. No.

995
01:38:15.096 --> 01:38:16.064
No what?

996
01:38:16.164 --> 01:38:19.684
I told you before.
don't touch the varnish.

997
01:38:19.768 --> 01:38:22.604
-That's not gonna be easy.
-If there's a problem.

998
01:38:22.704 --> 01:38:24.704
I'll do it myself.

999
01:38:26.308 --> 01:38:28.726
Look. the auction's in two weeks.

1000
01:38:28.810 --> 01:38:30.828
I have 16 other instruments.
Leroux's all over my ass.

1001
01:38:30.912 --> 01:38:32.964
I still have a Steiner I
haven't even touched.

1002
01:38:33.048 --> 01:38:35.250
I want complete LIGs. a resonance test.

1003
01:38:35.350 --> 01:38:38.153
mass specs and let's
get some varnish samples

1004
01:38:38.253 --> 01:38:40.687
all to the lab. okay?

1005
01:38:42.324 --> 01:38:44.976
This instrument is not a priority.

1006
01:38:45.060 --> 01:38:47.211
Every minute of my day is full.

1007
01:38:47.295 --> 01:38:48.797
That's fine.

1008
01:38:48.897 --> 01:38:51.417
We'll do this after hours. all right?

1009
01:38:58.940 --> 01:39:02.160
-These are the estimates?
-No. the reserves.

1010
01:39:02.244 --> 01:39:04.012
That we propose to the Chinese?

1011
01:39:04.112 --> 01:39:08.032
-Right.
-And what about these?

1012
01:39:08.116 --> 01:39:10.051
Those are some contentious items

1013
01:39:10.151 --> 01:39:12.101
you might not want to put on the block.

1014
01:39:12.187 --> 01:39:15.407
They're badly preserved
and hard to attribute.

1015
01:39:15.790 --> 01:39:17.975
What about that red one?

1016
01:39:18.059 --> 01:39:19.327
The red one?

1017
01:39:19.427 --> 01:39:22.647
Leroux seemed to think
it might be a Bussotti.

1018
01:39:24.199 --> 01:39:26.350
Yes.

1019
01:39:26.434 --> 01:39:27.936
It might be.

1020
01:39:28.036 --> 01:39:31.006
But the label's obscure
and the varnish is odd.

1021
01:39:31.106 --> 01:39:32.841
It's slightly opaque.

1022
01:39:32.941 --> 01:39:36.561
And I'm afraid as it stands
with no documentation...

1023
01:39:36.645 --> 01:39:38.645
And that's all you expect?

1024
01:39:56.731 --> 01:40:01.065
'With all my heart.'

1025
01:40:05.040 --> 01:40:08.593
You ever heard of the Red Violin?

1026
01:40:08.677 --> 01:40:11.696
Sure. sure... what...

1027
01:40:11.780 --> 01:40:14.816
the Frederick Pope Bussotti?
Sure. I heard stories.

1028
01:40:14.916 --> 01:40:16.751
How about copies?

1029
01:40:16.851 --> 01:40:18.869
There's one in London.
the only one I know of...

1030
01:40:18.953 --> 01:40:22.006
supposed to be copy commissioned by Pope.

1031
01:40:22.090 --> 01:40:25.787
-You know who has it?
-Some private collection.

1032
01:40:26.961 --> 01:40:31.816
You think I could...
buy it without tipping them off?

1033
01:40:31.900 --> 01:40:34.619
Tipping them off to what?

1034
01:40:34.703 --> 01:40:36.638
We know for sure we have a Bussotti.

1035
01:40:36.738 --> 01:40:38.089
I can date it within the year.

1036
01:40:38.173 --> 01:40:41.076
We still have this varnish
that doesn't configure

1037
01:40:41.176 --> 01:40:43.111
but we run some comparison tests

1038
01:40:43.211 --> 01:40:46.305
and see if this is the source of the copy.

1039
01:40:49.084 --> 01:40:52.536
You know I should
probably tell my employer?

1040
01:40:52.620 --> 01:40:54.823
If what you're saying is any way true

1041
01:40:54.923 --> 01:40:58.142
people could get a little...
excited.

1042
01:40:58.226 --> 01:41:00.428
You know I could lose my job over this?

1043
01:41:00.528 --> 01:41:03.481
Yes. I know.

1044
01:41:03.565 --> 01:41:05.816
You can go if you want to.

1045
01:41:05.900 --> 01:41:07.900
I can finish this myself.

1046
01:41:32.193 --> 01:41:36.393
Madame Leroux says that she has
to have catalog proofs today.

1047
01:41:37.766 --> 01:41:39.467
Are you finished?

1048
01:41:39.567 --> 01:41:42.153
Yes. they're back at my hotel.

1049
01:41:42.237 --> 01:41:44.237
I've been working at night.

1050
01:41:46.941 --> 01:41:48.893
Is there something else?

1051
01:41:48.977 --> 01:41:50.977
Oh.

1052
01:41:51.613 --> 01:41:54.899
Your wife called again.

1053
01:41:54.983 --> 01:41:57.042
Close the door. please.

1054
01:42:06.961 --> 01:42:09.947
Yes. is this the University of Montreal?

1055
01:42:10.031 --> 01:42:13.181
May I have the archeology
department. please?

1056
01:42:16.771 --> 01:42:20.057
Hi. this is Charles
Morritz over at Duval's.

1057
01:42:20.141 --> 01:42:23.151
I sent you some varnish
samples on Tuesday.

1058
01:42:24.712 --> 01:42:28.142
Yeah. I wanted you
to isolate an organic compound.

1059
01:43:06.821 --> 01:43:08.821
Excuse me.

1060
01:43:13.595 --> 01:43:16.180
May I have the manager. please?

1061
01:43:16.264 --> 01:43:18.349
Yes. the manager.

1062
01:43:18.433 --> 01:43:20.433
Well fine. put him on.

1063
01:43:22.504 --> 01:43:26.223
Yes. this is Mr. Morritz in 2703.

1064
01:43:26.307 --> 01:43:28.977
Listen. I want to make something
absolutely clear.

1065
01:43:29.077 --> 01:43:31.413
I don't want anyone coming to my room.

1066
01:43:31.513 --> 01:43:32.447
You understand?

1067
01:43:32.547 --> 01:43:35.399
Not the maid.
Not to check the minibar.

1068
01:43:35.483 --> 01:43:37.435
No chocolates on the pillow.

1069
01:43:37.519 --> 01:43:40.755
I'm giving your staff
sort of a break. understand?

1070
01:43:40.855 --> 01:43:43.073
No one is to come in my room

1071
01:43:43.157 --> 01:43:45.157
unless I request it.

1072
01:43:46.261 --> 01:43:48.261
Thank you.

1073
01:44:08.483 --> 01:44:11.101
-Yes.
-I got it.

1074
01:44:11.185 --> 01:44:13.871
It's coming.
I just talked to London.

1075
01:44:13.955 --> 01:44:15.906
Well. you know.
a little bit of smooth talk

1076
01:44:15.990 --> 01:44:18.720
and a little bit more money.
Your money.

1077
01:44:19.961 --> 01:44:22.341
You better make those phone calls.

1078
01:44:23.765 --> 01:44:26.917
Yeah. yeah. yeah. me too.

1079
01:44:27.001 --> 01:44:29.367
Well. actually...

1080
01:44:43.051 --> 01:44:45.002
-Wonderful.
-Yes.

1081
01:44:45.086 --> 01:44:47.104
I have the recording.

1082
01:44:47.188 --> 01:44:49.123
Pretty good Strad. don't you think?

1083
01:44:49.223 --> 01:44:51.392
I feel a little bit tight on the top.

1084
01:44:51.492 --> 01:44:54.378
A little bit stronger over the break.

1085
01:44:54.462 --> 01:44:57.882
To me it's very clean. precise.

1086
01:44:57.966 --> 01:45:01.652
Of course. it would
have to be played by a master.

1087
01:45:01.736 --> 01:45:03.304
What do you guess?

1088
01:45:03.404 --> 01:45:07.057
-1.7. 1.8 million.
-Not bad.

1089
01:45:07.141 --> 01:45:09.744
-Trust me on this.
-What else do you have?

1090
01:45:09.844 --> 01:45:12.380
That's about it.
But thanks for coming.

1091
01:45:12.480 --> 01:45:14.565
I hope you don't have
an orchestra waiting.

1092
01:45:14.649 --> 01:45:17.914
They can wait.
They can wait. no problem.

1093
01:45:20.188 --> 01:45:22.806
What about this here?

1094
01:45:22.890 --> 01:45:26.043
No. not that one.

1095
01:45:26.127 --> 01:45:30.086
-Nice little piece.
-But not for you.

1096
01:45:31.432 --> 01:45:34.518
-I will try it.
-No. no. no. Don't play it.

1097
01:45:34.602 --> 01:45:36.687
-Why not?
-Yes. why not?

1098
01:45:36.771 --> 01:45:39.557
I've just repaired it.
It's still fragile.

1099
01:45:39.641 --> 01:45:41.576
I don't even know why it's here.

1100
01:45:41.676 --> 01:45:44.611
I'll be very gentle.
Don't worry.

1101
01:46:37.765 --> 01:46:40.451
Yes. I see what you mean.

1102
01:46:40.535 --> 01:46:42.535
Nothing special.

1103
01:46:51.279 --> 01:46:53.279
How's it going?

1104
01:46:55.550 --> 01:46:58.953
What do you want me to do
with that one. the Pope copy?

1105
01:46:59.053 --> 01:47:02.039
I'll take it back to the hotel.

1106
01:47:02.123 --> 01:47:05.709
You got your money's worth.
That is a very good copy.

1107
01:47:05.793 --> 01:47:07.811
Nice violin.

1108
01:47:07.895 --> 01:47:10.681
but nothing like this one.

1109
01:47:10.765 --> 01:47:12.166
This...

1110
01:47:12.266 --> 01:47:15.719
is the single most
perfect acoustic machine

1111
01:47:15.803 --> 01:47:18.135
I have ever seen.

1112
01:47:20.575 --> 01:47:22.575
Amazing.

1113
01:47:32.253 --> 01:47:34.687
Guess I never thought I'd find it.

1114
01:47:38.626 --> 01:47:42.426
The ultimate...
thing as I see it.

1115
01:47:44.499 --> 01:47:47.051
The perfect marriage

1116
01:47:47.135 --> 01:47:49.086
of science

1117
01:47:49.170 --> 01:47:51.170
and beauty.

1118
01:47:51.906 --> 01:47:53.906
Impossible.

1119
01:47:56.577 --> 01:47:58.577
Now what?

1120
01:47:59.647 --> 01:48:04.234
What do you do when the thing
you most wanted so...

1121
01:48:04.318 --> 01:48:06.154
perfect...

1122
01:48:06.254 --> 01:48:08.381
just comes?

1123
01:48:14.962 --> 01:48:16.798
Do you have children?

1124
01:48:16.898 --> 01:48:18.332
Huh?

1125
01:48:18.432 --> 01:48:20.617
Children.
You have any?

1126
01:48:20.701 --> 01:48:22.720
No. no. I don't. but I know what you mean.

1127
01:48:22.804 --> 01:48:26.390
I would love to have this baby for myself.

1128
01:48:26.474 --> 01:48:27.875
Really?

1129
01:48:27.975 --> 01:48:30.728
What would you do?

1130
01:48:30.812 --> 01:48:34.398
Take it apart.
Find out how it works.

1131
01:48:34.482 --> 01:48:37.585
Take some igonmode readings
on the individual plates.

1132
01:48:37.685 --> 01:48:41.705
-I don't think you get it.
-Oh. yes. yes I do.

1133
01:48:41.789 --> 01:48:44.208
Take a look at this.

1134
01:48:44.292 --> 01:48:48.178
This is mode one.
.06 kHz.

1135
01:48:48.262 --> 01:48:50.662
Watch the response curve here.

1136
01:48:54.802 --> 01:48:57.168
I'll ease it up slowly for you.

1137
01:49:02.643 --> 01:49:05.237
Mode two.

1138
01:49:09.984 --> 01:49:12.145
Stop it.

1139
01:49:16.791 --> 01:49:19.176
-Bonjour. Mr. Morritz.
-Bonjour.

1140
01:49:19.260 --> 01:49:23.040
I have an envelope for you
from University of Montreal.

1141
01:49:24.532 --> 01:49:27.502
This says this arrived at 7:00.
I was in my room.

1142
01:49:27.602 --> 01:49:29.203
Yes. sir.

1143
01:49:29.303 --> 01:49:31.221
Why wasn't I notified?

1144
01:49:31.305 --> 01:49:32.656
You told us not to disturb you.

1145
01:49:32.740 --> 01:49:35.443
-Not for a courier.
-I didn't know. sir.

1146
01:49:35.543 --> 01:49:39.213
If a courier comes. you call me.
If a fax comes. you call me.

1147
01:49:39.313 --> 01:49:41.349
-Yes.
-It's important. do you get it?

1148
01:49:41.449 --> 01:49:44.051
You knock on my door
and you put it in my hand.

1149
01:49:44.151 --> 01:49:46.170
Comprende?

1150
01:49:46.254 --> 01:49:48.089
I need you to acknowledge.

1151
01:49:48.189 --> 01:49:50.189
Yes.

1152
01:49:53.628 --> 01:49:55.628
This is my business!

1153
01:53:40.287 --> 01:53:42.839
Mr. Morritz. I'm sorry.

1154
01:53:42.923 --> 01:53:46.160
You'd better come up.
I'm... they're waiting for you.

1155
01:53:46.260 --> 01:53:48.260
All right.

1156
01:53:52.266 --> 01:53:55.118
So nice of you to join us.

1157
01:53:55.202 --> 01:53:57.154
I hope you don't mind
us starting without you.

1158
01:53:57.238 --> 01:53:59.222
but there was the question
of some unusual expenses.

1159
01:53:59.306 --> 01:54:02.259
both here in the office

1160
01:54:02.343 --> 01:54:04.294
and at the hotel.

1161
01:54:04.378 --> 01:54:07.581
-Did you check my minibar too?
-It is our card. We are paying.

1162
01:54:07.681 --> 01:54:09.633
You made me wonder what
was going on down here.

1163
01:54:09.717 --> 01:54:11.867
so we decided to come
down and have a look.

1164
01:54:11.952 --> 01:54:14.104
and my. you have been busy.

1165
01:54:14.188 --> 01:54:16.440
a midst the courier bills

1166
01:54:16.524 --> 01:54:18.125
and DNA tests.

1167
01:54:18.225 --> 01:54:20.177
Very curious procedures.

1168
01:54:20.261 --> 01:54:22.479
Leroux has a theory.

1169
01:54:22.563 --> 01:54:24.656
Tell me if she's wrong.

1170
01:54:30.437 --> 01:54:34.874
Is our little red violin.
'The Red Violin'?

1171
01:54:41.849 --> 01:54:42.950
Yes.

1172
01:54:43.050 --> 01:54:45.035
I just wanted to be sure

1173
01:54:45.119 --> 01:54:46.420
before I told you.

1174
01:54:46.520 --> 01:54:49.639
This is very good news.

1175
01:54:49.723 --> 01:54:52.248
I'll set up a press release.

1176
01:54:55.930 --> 01:54:58.115
Good work.

1177
01:54:58.199 --> 01:55:00.034
Thank you.

1178
01:55:00.134 --> 01:55:02.636
Why don't you take
these last few days off?

1179
01:55:02.736 --> 01:55:05.170
Before you go home.

1180
01:55:10.477 --> 01:55:12.146
No.

1181
01:55:12.246 --> 01:55:14.646
No. I won't forget.

1182
01:55:15.816 --> 01:55:17.017
He lied.

1183
01:55:17.117 --> 01:55:21.404
He lied to me. And I knew it
as soon as I saw it.

1184
01:55:21.488 --> 01:55:23.615
And I said it.

1185
01:55:24.658 --> 01:55:28.059
This instrument should be mine.

1186
01:55:29.997 --> 01:55:31.997
Son of a bitch.

1187
01:56:28.856 --> 01:56:29.839
Ladies and gentlemen.

1188
01:56:29.923 --> 01:56:32.342
Duval's would like to welcome you

1189
01:56:32.426 --> 01:56:34.261
to this eagerly awaited event.

1190
01:56:34.361 --> 01:56:37.814
Our thanks to the government of China

1191
01:56:37.898 --> 01:56:41.751
for entrusting us
with this marvelous collection.

1192
01:56:41.835 --> 01:56:44.421
Thanks too to Madame Leroux.

1193
01:56:44.505 --> 01:56:48.091
who organized and
made possible this auction.

1194
01:56:48.175 --> 01:56:51.528
Let me remind you that
the conditions of sale

1195
01:56:51.612 --> 01:56:53.530
are listed in the catalog.

1196
01:56:53.614 --> 01:56:55.565
Before we begin. it is
my duty to direct you

1197
01:56:55.649 --> 01:56:57.567
to the conditions of sale

1198
01:56:57.651 --> 01:56:59.603
that you'll find at the
front of the catalog.

1199
01:56:59.687 --> 01:57:01.638
I will not read them
out loud at this point

1200
01:57:01.722 --> 01:57:04.213
but consider yourselves warned.

1201
01:57:05.259 --> 01:57:07.477
Now ladies and gentlemen.
we'll begin with lot number one.

1202
01:57:07.561 --> 01:57:09.430
Showing on the turntable on my right.

1203
01:57:09.530 --> 01:57:11.581
a fine French cello.

1204
01:57:11.665 --> 01:57:14.784
I'm gonna start with $10.000.

1205
01:57:14.868 --> 01:57:17.132
$10.000.

1206
01:57:46.133 --> 01:57:48.551
-Anything else?
-No.

1207
01:57:48.635 --> 01:57:51.035
-Which airport. sir?
-Dorval.

1208
01:57:56.677 --> 01:57:59.271
There is one stop we have to make.

1209
01:58:02.449 --> 01:58:03.800
$400.000 at the back of the room.

1210
01:58:03.884 --> 01:58:06.169
The Stradivarius now at 400.000.

1211
01:58:06.253 --> 01:58:09.339
Against the telephone. 420.000.
450.000.

1212
01:58:09.423 --> 01:58:11.608
Against you. sir.
500.000.

1213
01:58:11.692 --> 01:58:15.312
500.000 back to the front.
500.000.500.000.

1214
01:58:15.396 --> 01:58:16.880
Wait here. I'll just be a minute.

1215
01:58:16.964 --> 01:58:18.899
I might have to go around the block.

1216
01:58:18.999 --> 01:58:21.160
All right. if you have to.

1217
01:58:28.108 --> 01:58:31.161
1.100.000.
1.100.000.

1218
01:58:31.245 --> 01:58:32.546
1.200.000.

1219
01:58:32.646 --> 01:58:34.348
Is that a bid. sir?
Don't be shy.

1220
01:58:34.448 --> 01:58:36.717
All right then. I'll take it.
1.300.000.

1221
01:58:36.817 --> 01:58:38.552
1.400.000.

1222
01:58:38.652 --> 01:58:40.904
1.500.000.
Yes. sir. I've got you.

1223
01:58:40.988 --> 01:58:43.640
$1.600.000.
1.600.000.

1224
01:58:43.724 --> 01:58:46.443
Not you. sir?
1.650.000.

1225
01:58:46.527 --> 01:58:48.128
1.675.000.

1226
01:58:48.228 --> 01:58:50.364
-Not yours. ma'am.
-Mr. Morritz.

1227
01:58:50.464 --> 01:58:53.016
Please don't let me forget this.

1228
01:58:53.100 --> 01:58:55.969
Against the telephone now.
Against you. sir.

1229
01:58:56.069 --> 01:58:57.571
1.810.000.

1230
01:58:57.671 --> 01:59:02.192
1.850.000.
1.875.000 in the room.

1231
01:59:02.276 --> 01:59:03.977
1.900.000.

1232
01:59:04.077 --> 01:59:05.713
1.900.000.

1233
01:59:05.813 --> 01:59:07.997
1.900.000 on the telephone.

1234
01:59:08.081 --> 01:59:09.999
1.920.000 in the room.

1235
01:59:10.083 --> 01:59:12.001
1.920.000. I've got you. sir.
Thank you.

1236
01:59:12.085 --> 01:59:13.654
1.940.000.

1237
01:59:13.754 --> 01:59:16.706
Not yours. ma'am.
Neither of yours.

1238
01:59:16.790 --> 01:59:20.610
$1.940.000.

1239
01:59:20.694 --> 01:59:22.262
Son of a bitch.

1240
01:59:22.362 --> 01:59:23.797
I'll take 10.000.000.

1241
01:59:23.897 --> 01:59:26.116
You want back in. sir?

1242
01:59:26.200 --> 01:59:28.284
Is that a yes?
No.

1243
01:59:28.368 --> 01:59:31.521
The Stradivarius now at $1.940.000.

1244
01:59:31.605 --> 01:59:33.723
Not yours. ma'am.

1245
01:59:33.807 --> 01:59:37.594
Neither of yours.
$1.940.000.

1246
01:59:37.678 --> 01:59:39.079
Against you all in the room.

1247
01:59:39.179 --> 01:59:40.948
Is that all then?

1248
01:59:41.048 --> 01:59:43.066
Fair warning.

1249
01:59:43.150 --> 01:59:44.451
1.950.000 on my left.

1250
01:59:44.551 --> 01:59:48.638
Down to you two now.
1.950.000.

1251
01:59:48.722 --> 01:59:50.940
Not yours. sir?
Not yours. Paul?

1252
01:59:51.024 --> 01:59:52.976
The bid is 1.950.000.

1253
01:59:53.060 --> 01:59:55.278
-Did you clean this?
-Against you all in the room.

1254
01:59:55.362 --> 01:59:56.880
-Who's responsible for...
-The Stradivarius now

1255
01:59:56.964 --> 01:59:58.499
at 1.950.000.

1256
01:59:58.599 --> 02:00:00.683
-I have to get the last lot.
-All done then.

1257
02:00:00.767 --> 02:00:02.085
-I come to fix...
-Excuse me...

1258
02:00:02.169 --> 02:00:04.120
-... I asked the client...
-What's going on?

1259
02:00:04.204 --> 02:00:07.157
-We're gonna have to...
-$1.950.000.

1260
02:00:07.241 --> 02:00:09.971
And sold to the lady on my left.

1261
02:00:16.083 --> 02:00:18.519
The last sale of the evening.
lot number 72.

1262
02:00:18.619 --> 02:00:19.920
on the turntable there.

1263
02:00:20.020 --> 02:00:23.406
-Wait!
-The star of the night...

1264
02:00:23.490 --> 02:00:24.774
-The tag!
-The last violin

1265
02:00:24.858 --> 02:00:27.644
of Niccolò Bussotti. 1681.
A master...

1266
02:00:27.728 --> 02:00:29.946
I put the tag on myself!

1267
02:00:30.030 --> 02:00:32.382
If she will give us the pleasure.

1268
02:00:32.466 --> 02:00:34.466
Too late.

1269
02:00:35.135 --> 02:00:37.353
Here she is now. lot 72.

1270
02:00:37.437 --> 02:00:40.190
the so-called Red Violin.

1271
02:00:40.274 --> 02:00:41.791
-Here we go now.
-The last order bid...

1272
02:00:41.875 --> 02:00:44.427
Call security.

1273
02:00:44.511 --> 02:00:47.781
So. we'll open the floor
and who will start us off?

1274
02:00:47.881 --> 02:00:50.300
260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

1275
02:00:50.384 --> 02:00:52.252
270.000.
Suzanne on the telephone.

1276
02:00:52.352 --> 02:00:54.370
280.000.
Back to you. sir.

1277
02:00:54.454 --> 02:00:56.539
-Here.
-300.000 in the back.

1278
02:00:56.623 --> 02:00:59.175
320.000.
I see you. Suzanne.

1279
02:00:59.259 --> 02:01:01.578
340.000.
340.000 now in the front.

1280
02:01:01.662 --> 02:01:04.747
400.000 at the back of the hall.
420.000.

1281
02:01:04.831 --> 02:01:08.051
500.000.500.000.
Against the telephone now.

1282
02:01:08.135 --> 02:01:09.085
-Suzanne...
-500.000.

1283
02:01:09.169 --> 02:01:10.938
-stop it.
-Is that a yes? No?

1284
02:01:11.038 --> 02:01:12.873
Against you. sir.

1285
02:01:12.973 --> 02:01:15.425
600.000.
700.000.

1286
02:01:15.509 --> 02:01:17.927
Not yours. sir.
Not yours.

1287
02:01:18.011 --> 02:01:21.064
I have $800.000.

1288
02:01:21.148 --> 02:01:23.967
$900.000.

1289
02:01:24.051 --> 02:01:26.836
$1.000.000.
Mr. Ruselsky.

1290
02:01:26.920 --> 02:01:30.240
$1.100.000.
1.200.000.

1291
02:01:30.324 --> 02:01:32.942
Not you. sir?
Ma'am?

1292
02:01:33.026 --> 02:01:34.728
-1.200.000.
-Are you sure?

1293
02:01:34.828 --> 02:01:37.113
1.300.000.
1.400.000.

1294
02:01:37.197 --> 02:01:38.999
1.400.000.

1295
02:01:39.099 --> 02:01:39.833
1.500.000.

1296
02:01:39.933 --> 02:01:42.163
1.600.000.

1297
02:01:46.506 --> 02:01:49.492
-Mr. Morritz.
-Down to you two now.

1298
02:01:49.576 --> 02:01:52.495
-2.000.000. Mr. Ruselsky.
-Mr. Morritz!

1299
02:01:52.579 --> 02:01:55.565
-Mr. Morritz.
-2.100.000.

1300
02:01:55.649 --> 02:01:57.050
2.200.000.

1301
02:01:57.150 --> 02:01:59.150
Mr. Morritz!

1302
02:02:00.687 --> 02:02:02.556
Excuse me.

1303
02:02:02.656 --> 02:02:04.591
Is this what you're looking for?

1304
02:02:04.691 --> 02:02:08.422
-Down to you two. 2.200.000.
-Yes.

1305
02:02:09.496 --> 02:02:10.564
Your coat.

1306
02:02:10.664 --> 02:02:12.065
2.200.000.

1307
02:02:12.165 --> 02:02:14.918
2.300.000.

1308
02:02:15.002 --> 02:02:16.770
2.400.000.

1309
02:02:16.870 --> 02:02:18.870
Merci.

1310
02:02:20.674 --> 02:02:23.643
$2.400.000.

1311
02:02:25.846 --> 02:02:27.846
Is that all then?

1312
